  [ // 40:3
   ['And in those days John the Immerser* comes, preaching in the wilderness of Judea,'],
   ['and saying, Repent; for* the kingdom of heaven has drawn near.'],
   ['For* this is he who was spoken of by Isaiah the prophet, saying, &lsquo;The voice of one crying in the wilderness, prepare the way of the Lord, make* his paths straight.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 40:3}</font>'],
   ['Now John himself had his outer clothing made of camel&rsquo;s hair and a leather belt around his waist, and his nourishment was locusts and wild honey.'],
   ['Then Jerusalem and all Judea and all the people of the region around the Jordan were going out to him.'],
