  [ // 40:4
   ['Then Jesus was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the Devil.'],
   ['And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights, later he hungered.'],
   ['And the Tempter came and said to him, If you are the Son of God, speak, in order that these stones may become bread.'],
   ['But answering, he said, <font color=#FF0000>It has been written, &lsquo;Man will not live on bread alone, but on every word that goes out through the mouth of God!&rsquo;</font> <font color=#808080>{Deut. 8:3}</font>'],
   ['Then the Devil takes him into the holy city. And he stands him upon the pinnacle of the temple,'],
   ['and says to him, If you are the Son of God, cast yourself downward; for* it has been written, &lsquo;He will command the messengers concerning you, and they will lift you up upon their hands, lest you might hit your foot against a stone. &rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ps. 91:11f}</font>'],
   ['Jesus said to him, <font color=#FF0000>Again it has been written, &lsquo;You will not test the Lord, your God.&rsquo;</font> <font color=#808080>{Deut. 6:16}</font>'],
   ['Again, the Devil takes him to an exceedingly high mountain and shows him all the kingdoms of the world and the glory of them;'],
