  [ // 42:14
   ['And it happened, when he went into the house of one of the rulers of the Pharisees on a Sabbath to eat bread, that they were observing him.'],
   ['And behold, there was in front of him a certain man having dropsy.'],
   ['And answering Jesus spoke to the professors of the law and Pharisees, saying,<font color=#FF0000> Is it legal to heal on the Sabbath?</font>'],
   ['But they were quiet. And he took him and healed him and dismissed him.'],
   ['And answering, he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Which </font><i><font color=#FF0000>one</font></i><font color=#FF0000> of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> </font><i><font color=#FF0000>if</font></i><font color=#FF0000> a son or a bull will fall into a well and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will not immediately pull him up on the Sabbath day?</font>'],
   ['And they are not strong-enough answer back to him as to these things.'],
   ['And he spoke a parable to those who were invited, when he took-heed of how they chose out the foremost-places; saying to them:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Whenever you are invited by anyone to a marriage feast, do not recline in the foremost seat; lest a more admired man </font><i><font color=#FF0000>than</font></i><font color=#FF0000> you may have been invited by him,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and he who invited you and him will come and say to you, Give this man </font><i><font color=#FF0000>your</font></i><font color=#FF0000> place, and then you may begin with shame to hold the lowest place.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But whenever you are invited, go and lean-back in the lowest place; that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> whenever he who has invited you comes, he may say to you, Friend, go higher toward </font><i><font color=#FF0000>me</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and then you will have glory before those who recline</font><i><font color=#FF0000> at the table</font></i><font color=#FF0000> with you.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because everyone who is exalting himself will be humbled, and he who is humbling himself will be exalted.</font>'],
   ['And he said to him who had also invited him, <font color=#FF0000>Whenever you make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a meal or a supper, do not summon your friends, nor your brethren, nor your relatives, nor rich neighbors; lest they may also invite you too and it may become a repayment for you.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But whenever you make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a banquet, invite the poor, the disabled, the lame, the blind;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and you will be fortunate, because they do not have </font><i><font color=#FF0000>anything in which</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to repay you; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you will be repaid in the resurrection of the righteous.</font>'],
   ['And when one of those who reclined at the meal with him heard these things, he said to him, He who will eat bread in the kingdom of God is fortunate.'],
   ['But he said to him, <font color=#FF0000>A certain</font> <font color=#FF0000>man made</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a great supper, and he invited many;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and he sent forth his bondservant in the hour of supper to say to those who were invited, Come, because all things are already prepared.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And they all with one </font><i><font color=#FF0000>desire</font></i><font color=#FF0000> began to excuse themselves. The first said to him, I have bought a field and I have a necessity to go out and to see it; I request you have me excused.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And another said, I have bought five yoke of bulls and I </font><i><font color=#FF0000>must</font></i><font color=#FF0000> go to test them; I request you have me excused.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And another said, I have married a wife and therefore I cannot come.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And that bondservant came and reported to his lord these things. Then the householder being angry said to his bondservant, Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city and bring the poor and disabled and lame and blind in here.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the bondservant said, Lord, it has happened as you commanded and there is still </font><i><font color=#FF0000>more</font></i><font color=#FF0000> places.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the lord said to the bondservant, Go out into the roads and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>over the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> fences and urge </font><i><font color=#FF0000>them</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to come in, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> my house may be filled.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> that none of those men who were invited will taste of my supper.</font>'],
   ['Now there traveled together with him great crowds and he turned and said to them,'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>If anyone comes to me and does not hate his own father and mother and </font>wife and children and brethren and sisters, and also, still his own life, he cannot be my disciple.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And whoever does not bear his own cross and come after me, cannot be my disciple.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> which out of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, wishing to build a tower, does not first sit down and calculate the cost, if he has the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>means</font></i><font color=#FF0000> toward </font><i><font color=#FF0000>its</font></i><font color=#FF0000> completion?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Lest, when he has laid a foundation and is not strong-enough to finish, all who view </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> may begin to mock him,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>saying, This man began to build and was not strong-enough to finish.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Or what king, as he is going to encounter another king in war, will not sit down first and counsel if he is able with ten-thousand to meet him who is coming against him with twenty thousand?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Otherwise </font><i><font color=#FF0000>while</font></i><font color=#FF0000> he is still faraway, having sent an ambassador, he asks for the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>terms</font></i><font color=#FF0000> of peace.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore so everyone out of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> who does not bid farewell to all that he possesses, he is not able to be my disciple.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The salt is good, but if the salt is flavorless, what shall it be seasoned with?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>It is fit neither </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>for the soil nor </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>for the manure-pile. Cast it outside. He who has ears to hear, let him hear.</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:15
   ['Now all the tax collectors and sinners were drawing near to him to hear him.'],
   ['And the Pharisees and the scribes murmured, saying, This man accepts sinners and eats with them.'],
   ['And he spoke to them this parable, saying:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>What man out of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, having a hundred sheep and having lost one out of them, does not leave the ninety nine in the wilderness and go after what is lost, until he should find it?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And when he has found it, he places it upon his shoulders, rejoicing.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And when he comes to his house, he calls together his friends and his neighbors, saying to them, Rejoice with me, because I have found my sheep which was lost.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> thus, that there will be joy in heaven over one sinner who repents, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>more</font></i><font color=#FF0000> than over ninety nine righteous </font><i><font color=#FF0000>ones</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, who need no repentance.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Or what woman having ten two-denarius coins, if she loses one two-denarius coin, does not light a lamp and sweep the house and seek carefully until she should find it?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And when she has found it, she calls together her friends and her neighbors, saying, Rejoice with me, because I have found the two-denarius coin which I had lost.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Even so, I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, There is joy before the messengers of God over one sinner who repents.</font>'],
   ['And he said, <font color=#FF0000>A certain man had two sons.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the younger of them said to </font><i><font color=#FF0000>his</font></i><font color=#FF0000> father, Father give </font><i><font color=#FF0000>me</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the part of the estate </font><i><font color=#FF0000>that would be</font></i><font color=#FF0000> put </font><i><font color=#FF0000>toward me</font></i><font color=#FF0000>. And he sections his livelihood to them.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And not many days after, the younger son gathered all together and went abroad into a far country, and he squandered his estate with riotous living there.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And when he had spent all, there was a mighty famine in that country, and he began to fall-short </font><i><font color=#FF0000>of things</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he went and joined himself to one of the citizens of that country, and he sent him into his field to feed swine.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he desired to fill his belly from the carob pods that the swine ate and no one gave </font><i><font color=#FF0000>anything</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But when he came to himself he said, How many of my father&rsquo;s hired </font><i><font color=#FF0000>servants</font></i><font color=#FF0000> have an abundance of bread? But I am perishing </font><i><font color=#FF0000>here</font></i><font color=#FF0000> in famine!</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I will stand up and go to my father and will say to him, Father, I have sinned at heaven and in your sight.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I am no more worthy to be called your son. Make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> me like one of your hired </font><i><font color=#FF0000>servants.</font></i>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And standing up, he came to his father. But while he was afar, distant, his father saw him and had compassion and </font>ran and fell upon his neck and kissed him.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the son said to him, Father, I have sinned toward heaven and in your sight. I am no more worthy to be called your son.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But the father said to his bondservants, Bring out the chief robe and clothe him, and give </font><i><font color=#FF0000>him</font></i><font color=#FF0000> a ring </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>for his hand and shoes </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>for his feet;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and bring the fattened calf and sacrifice </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>when</font></i><font color=#FF0000> eating </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it,</font></i> <font color=#FF0000>we should be joyous.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because this </font><i><font color=#FF0000>one</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, my son, was dead and is alive again and he was lost and is found. And they began to be joyous.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Now his elder son was in the field and as he came and drew near to the house, he heard harmony and dancing.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he called to him one of the young-servants and inquired what these things might be.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said to him, Your brother is coming, and your father has sacrificed the fattened calf, because he has received him </font><i><font color=#FF0000>back</font></i><font color=#FF0000> healthy.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But he was angry and was not willing to go in and therefore his father came out and encouraged him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But answering, he said to </font><i><font color=#FF0000>his</font></i><font color=#FF0000> father, Behold, I </font><i><font color=#FF0000>did</font></i><font color=#FF0000> serve</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> so-many years, and I never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> passed over a commandment of yours, and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>yet</font></i><font color=#FF0000> you never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> gave me a </font><i><font color=#FF0000>young</font></i><font color=#FF0000> goat, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I might be joyous with my friends.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But when this your son came, who has devoured your livelihood with harlots, you sacrificed the fattened calf for him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said to him, Child, you are always with me and all that is mine is yours.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But it was essential </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for us</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to be joyous and rejoice, because this </font><i><font color=#FF0000>one</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, your brother was dead and is alive again, and was lost and is found.</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:16
   ['And he also said to his disciples, <font color=#FF0000>There was a certain rich man, who had a steward, and this one was indicted by him when </font><i><font color=#FF0000>he was found</font></i><font color=#FF0000> squandering his possessions.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And having summoned him, he said to him, What is this that I am hearing concerning you? Give </font><i><font color=#FF0000>me</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the account of your stewardship; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you can no longer be a steward.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the steward said with himself, What should I do, because my lord is taking away the stewardship from me? I am not strong-enough to dig; I am ashamed to beg.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know what I should do, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> whenever I am removed </font><i><font color=#FF0000>from</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the stewardship, they may accept me into their houses.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And calling to him each one of his lord&rsquo;s debtors, he said to the first, How much do you owe to my lord?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said, A hundred</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>eight-gallon containers of oil.</font> And he said to him, Take <i><font color=#FF0000>out</font></i><font color=#FF0000> your</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>contract and sit down quickly and write fifty.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Thereafter he said to another and how much do you owe?</font> And he said, A hundred twelve-bushel containers of grain. And he says to him, Accept your<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>contract and write eighty.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And his lord praised the steward of unrighteousness because he had done prudently, because the sons of this world are more prudent to their own generation; over the sons of the light.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, Make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> friends for yourselves</font> <font color=#FF0000>out of the money of unrighteousness; that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, whenever it fails, they may accept you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> into the everlasting tabernacles.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who is faithful in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> least </font><i><font color=#FF0000>matters</font></i><font color=#FF0000> is also faithful in much and he who is unrighteous in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> least </font><i><font color=#FF0000>matters</font></i><font color=#FF0000> is also unrighteous in much.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore if you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have not become faithful in the unrighteous money, who will entrust the true </font><i><font color=#FF0000>riches</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And if you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have not become faithful in what is another&rsquo;s, who </font>will give you<font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> what is your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> own?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>No domestic </font><i><font color=#FF0000>servant</font></i><font color=#FF0000> is able to serve</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> two lords; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> either he will hate the one and love</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the other; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> either he will hold to one and despise the other. You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are not able to serve</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> God and money.</font>'],
   ['And the Pharisees, who are* money-lovers, also heard all these things, and they ridiculed him.'],
   ['And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are those who are justifying yourselves in the sight of men, but God knows your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hearts, because what is exalted among men </font><i><font color=#FF0000>is</font></i><font color=#FF0000> an abomination in the sight of God.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The law and the prophets </font><i><font color=#FF0000>were</font></i><font color=#FF0000> until John; from that time the good-news of the kingdom of God is proclaimed and everyone violently-enters into it.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But it is easier </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the heaven and the earth to</font> <font color=#FF0000>pass away, than </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> one serif of the law to fall short.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Everyone who divorces his wife and marries another, is committing adultery and everyone who marries </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> one who is divorced from a husband is committing adultery.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Now there was a certain rich man and he was clothed in purple and fine-linen, having been radiantly joyous every day.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And there was a certain poor </font><i><font color=#FF0000>man</font></i><font color=#FF0000> named Lazarus, who was laid at his gate, being full of sores,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and desiring to be fed from the crumbs that fell from the rich man&rsquo;s table. But even the dogs came and licked his sores.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And it happened, that the poor </font><i><font color=#FF0000>man</font></i><font color=#FF0000> died and that he was carried away by the messengers into Abraham&rsquo;s bosom and the rich man also died and was buried.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And in Hades he lifted up his eyes, being</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in torments and he sees Abraham from afar and Lazarus in his bosom.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And shouting, he said, Father Abraham, have mercy on me and send Lazarus, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> he may dip the tip of his finger in water and may cool my tongue, because I am in anguish in this flame.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But Abraham said, Child, remember that you received your good things in your life and Lazarus likewise evil things, but now he is comforted here and you are in anguish.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And upon all things, a great chasm is established between us and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>that those who wish to cross over from here to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may not be able, nor may they ferry over from there to us.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said, Therefore I am requesting </font><i><font color=#FF0000>from</font></i><font color=#FF0000> you, father, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you should send him to my father&rsquo;s house; </font>18 <font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I have five brethren; </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>that he may testify to them, in order that they may also not come into this place of torment.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But Abraham says to him, They have Moses and the prophets. Let them hear them.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said, No, father Abraham, but if someone goes to them from the dead, they will repent.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said to him, If they do not hear Moses and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded, if someone rises</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> up from the dead.</font><font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Lk 16:6-7 Greek: writings.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:17
   ['And he said to his disciples,<font color=#FF0000> It is inevitable that offenses might come, but woe </font><i><font color=#FF0000>to him</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, through whom they come!</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>It is beneficial for him if a millstone rotated by a donkey encompassed his neck and he were tossed into the sea, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>rather</font></i><font color=#FF0000> than that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> he should offend one of these little ones.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Take-heed to yourselves; and if your brother sins </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#FF0000> against you, rebuke him, and if he repents, forgive him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And if he </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#FF0000> sins against you seven times in the day and should turn again to you seven times </font>in the day, saying, I repent. You will forgive him.'],
   ['And the apostles said to the Lord, Add to our faith<font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['And the Lord said,<font color=#FF0000> If you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have faith like a kernel of a mustard-seed, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> might say to this mulberry tree, Be uprooted and be planted in the sea, and it would obey</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But which one out of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, having a bondservant plowing or tending the flock, will say </font><i><font color=#FF0000>to him</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, when he has come in from the field, Come immediately and lean-back </font><i><font color=#FF0000>at the table.</font></i>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But will you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> not, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>rather</font></i><font color=#FF0000> say to him, Prepare something </font><i><font color=#FF0000>so</font></i><font color=#FF0000> I may dine. And when you gird yourself, serve me, while I eat and drink, and you may eat and may drink after these things.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He does not </font><i><font color=#FF0000>give</font></i><font color=#FF0000> gratitude to that bondservant because he did the things </font><i><font color=#FF0000>that were</font></i><font color=#FF0000> commanded him, does he? I think not.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>So also you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, whenever you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have done all the things that are commanded you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, say, We are useless bondservants because we have done what we were obligated to do.</font> <font color=#808080>{Lk 17:11-37; Borders of Samaria and Galilee; Lk 18:1-14; early 30 AD.}</font>'],
   ['And it happened, as he was traveling to Jerusalem, that he was going through the middle of Samaria and Galilee.'],
   ['And as he entered into a certain village, ten men who were lepers met him there, who stood farther out;'],
   ['and they lifted up their voices, saying, Jesus, Master*, have mercy on us.'],
   ['And when he saw them, he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Go and show yourselves to the priests.</font> And it happened, as they went, they were cleansed.'],
   ['And one out of them, when he saw that he was healed, turned back, with a loud voice glorifying God;'],
   ['and he fell upon his face beside his feet, giving-thanks to him and he was a Samaritan.'],
   ['And answering, Jesus said,<font color=#FF0000> Were</font> <font color=#FF0000>there not ten cleansed? But where </font><i><font color=#FF0000>were</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the nine?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Was there no one found, except this immigrant, who returned to give glory to God?</font>'],
   ['And he said to him, <font color=#FF0000>Stand and go your way. Your faith has cured you.</font>'],
   ['And being asked by the Pharisees when the kingdom of God is coming, he answered them and said, <font color=#FF0000>The kingdom of God is not coming with observation;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>nor will they say, Behold, here! Or, behold there! For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behold, the kingdom of God is within you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['And he said to the disciples, <font color=#FF0000>The days will come, when you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will desire to see one of the days of the Son of Man and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will not see it.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And they will say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, Behold, here! Behold, there! Do not go away, nor should you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> pursue </font><i><font color=#FF0000>them</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> just-like the lightning, which flashes from the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>one end</font></i><font color=#FF0000> under heaven, shines to the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>other end</font></i><font color=#FF0000> under heaven; so will the Son of Man be in his day.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But he must first suffer many things and be rejected</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> by this generation.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And as it happened in the days of Noah, so it will also be in the days of the Son of Man.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>They ate, they drank, they married, they were betrothed, until the day that Noah entered into the ark and the flood came and destroyed them all.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Likewise even as it happened in the days of Lot; they ate, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they built;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>but in the day that Lot went out from Sodom it rained fire and brimstone from heaven and destroyed them all.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>According to the same things, it will be in the day that the Son of Man is revealed.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>In that day, he who will be upon the housetop and his goods in the house, let him not go down to take them away and let him who is in the field likewise not turn back.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Remember Lot&rsquo;s wife.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000></font>Whoever seeks to save his life, will lose it, but whoever loses <i><font color=#FF0000>it,</font></i><font color=#FF0000> will preserve </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, There will be two men upon one bed in that night; the one will be taken and the other will be left.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>There will be two </font><i><font color=#FF0000>women </font></i><font color=#FF0000>grinding together; the one will be taken and the other will be left.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><i><font color=#FF0000>There will be two men in the field; the one will be taken and the other will be left.</font></i><font color=#FF0000></font>'],
   ['And they answering say to him, Where, Lord? And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Where the body </font><i><font color=#FF0000>is</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, the vultures will also be gathered together there.</font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Lk 17:3,4 - Greek: into, toward. Lk 17:36 is not found in the majority of Greek texts. Early attempt to harmonize the gospels; See Mt. 24:40}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:18
   ['And he also spoke a parable to them, to show that, it is essential for them to always pray and not to be depressed;'],
   ['saying:<font color=#FF0000> A certain judge was in a certain city, who did not fear God and did not revere man.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And a widow was in that city, and she came often to him, saying, Avenge me of my opponent.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he did not wish to, for a time, but after these things, he said with himself, Even if I do not fear God, and do not revere man;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>yet because this widow is harassing me, I will avenge her, in order that she may not pester me, coming </font><i><font color=#FF0000>often</font></i><font color=#FF0000> </font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>for an end </font><i><font color=#FF0000>of her opponent</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['And the Lord said, <font color=#FF0000>Hear what the judge of unrighteousness</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>said.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Now should God not do the avenging of his chosen, who are crying to him day and night? Also </font><i><font color=#FF0000>should he not</font></i><font color=#FF0000> be patient over them?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> that he will do the avenging on them quickly.</font> However, when the Son of Man comes, will he find the faith upon the earth?'],
   ['And he spoke this parable to some who have confidence in themselves that they were righteous and scorning the rest:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Two men went up into the temple to pray; the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>first</font></i><font color=#FF0000> one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The Pharisee stood and prayed these things with himself, God, I give-thanks to you, that I am not like the rest of men: swindlers, unrighteous, adulterers or just-like this tax collector.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I fast twice in the week; I tithe of all things, as many </font><i><font color=#FF0000>things</font></i><font color=#FF0000> as I procure.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the tax collector, standing from afar, did not even wish to lift up his eyes to heaven, but beat his chest, saying, God, be lenient to me the sinner.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, This man went down to his house justified </font><i><font color=#FF0000>rather</font></i><font color=#FF0000> than the other, because everyone who is exalting himself will be humbled, but he who is humbling himself will be exalted.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 10:13-16 &amp; Mt 19:13-15 &amp; Lk 18:15-17 Peraea</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And they were also bringing to him their babies, that* he might touch them, but when the disciples saw it, they rebuked them.'],
   ['But Jesus having called them to him, said,<font color=#FF0000> Allow the little children to come to me and do not forbid them; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the kingdom of God is for such.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Assuredly I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, Whoever does not accept the kingdom of God like a little child, he may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> enter into it.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 10:17-31 &amp; Mt 19:16-20:16 &amp; Lk 18:18-30 Peraea</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And a certain ruler asked him, saying, Good Teacher, what shall I do to inherit everlasting life?'],
   ['And Jesus said to him, <font color=#FF0000>Why do you call me good? None is good, except one, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>our</font></i><font color=#FF0000> God.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>You know the commandments: &lsquo;Do not commit adultery. Do not murder. Do not steal. Do not falsely testify. Honor your father and your mother.&rsquo; </font><font color=#808080>{Ex. 20:12-16 &amp; Deut. 5:16-20}</font>'],
   ['And he said, I have observed all these things from my youth up.'],
   ['And when Jesus heard these things, he said to him,<font color=#FF0000> One thing is still lacking</font>*<font color=#FF0000> for you. Sell all things, as many </font><i><font color=#FF0000>things</font></i><font color=#FF0000> as you have and distribute to the poor and you will have treasure in heaven and come-here. Follow me.</font>'],
   ['But when he heard these things, he became very sorrowful; for* he was extremely rich.'],
   ['And Jesus seeing him when he became very sorrowful, said, <font color=#FF0000>How those who have wealth will hardly enter into the kingdom of God!</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> it is easier </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> a camel to enter in through a needle&rsquo;s eye, than </font><i><font color=#FF0000>for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.</font>'],
   ['And those who heard it said, Then who can be saved?'],
   ['But he said,<font color=#FF0000> The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.</font>'],
   ['And Peter said, Behold, we left all and followed you.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Assuredly I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, There is no one who has left </font><i><font color=#FF0000>his</font></i><font color=#FF0000> house or parents or brethren or children, because of the kingdom of God,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>who may not receive again much more in this time and in the world to come everlasting life.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 10:32-45 &amp; Mt 20:17-28 &amp; Lk 18:31-34; Peraea or Judea, near Jordan</font><font color=#808080>}</font><font color=#FF0000></font>'],
   ['And he took the twelve with him and said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem and all the things that are written through the prophets will be accomplished by the Son of Man.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> he will be given up to the Gentiles and will be mocked and insulted and spit on;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and they will scourge and kill him and he will rise</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> up in the third day.</font>'],
   ['And they understood none of these things, and this saying was hid from them and they did not know the things which was said.<font color=#808080> {Mk 10:46-52 &amp; Mt 20:29-34 &amp; Lk 18:35-43; Jericho}</font>'],
   ['And it happened, as he drew near to Jericho, a certain blind man sat by the road begging.'],
   ['And hearing a crowd traveling through, he inquired what this might be.'],
   ['And they reported to him, that Jesus the Nazarene is passing by.'],
   ['And he cried out, saying, Jesus, son of David, have mercy on me.'],
   ['And those preceding, rebuked him that* he should be silent but he cried out much more, Son of David, have mercy on me!'],
   ['And Jesus stood still and commanded him to be led to him and when he drew near, he asked him,'],
   ['saying, <font color=#FF0000>What do you wish that I might do for you?</font> And he said, Lord, that* I may recover my sight.'],
   ['And Jesus said to him,<font color=#FF0000> Recover your sight. Your faith has cured you.</font>'],
   ['And instantly he recovered his sight and followed him, glorifying God and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise to God.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Lk 18:6 Literally: says (but speaks of previous verses). Lk 18:13- OR be propitiated, be atoning.}</font> <font color=#808080> {Lk 19:1-28; Jericho}</font>'],
  ],
  [ // 42:19
   ['And he entered and was going through Jericho.'],
   ['And behold, a man called by the name Zacchaeus was there and he was a chief tax collector and he was rich.'],
   ['And he was seeking to see Jesus; who he is, and could not from the crowd, because he was little in stature.'],
   ['And he ran ahead in front of the crowd and goes up into a sycamore tree that* he might see him, because he was about to go through that way.'],
   ['And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up and saw him and said to him,<font color=#FF0000> Zacchaeus, hurry and come down; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I must abide in your house today.</font>'],
   ['And having hurried, he came down and accepted him, rejoicing.'],
   ['And when they saw it, they all murmured, saying, He goes to board with a man who is a sinner.'],
   ['And Zacchaeus stood and said to the Lord, Behold, Lord, I give half of my possessions to the poor and if I have cheated anyone of anything, I repay them four times that.'],
   ['And Jesus said to him,<font color=#FF0000> Today salvation has come to this house, insomuch as he is also a son of Abraham.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the Son of Man came to seek and save what was lost.</font>'],
   ['And as they heard these things, he added and spoke a parable, because he was near to Jerusalem and because they supposed that the kingdom of God was to instantly appear.'],
   ['Therefore he said: <font color=#FF0000>A certain nobleman went into a far </font><i><font color=#FF0000>away</font></i><font color=#FF0000> country, to receive for himself a kingdom and to return.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he called ten bondservants of his and gave them ten two-hundred denarius coins and said to them, You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> trade </font><i><font color=#FF0000>with this</font></i><font color=#FF0000> until I come.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But his citizens hated him and sent an ambassador after him, saying, We do not wish that this man reign over us.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And it happened, when he had come back again, having received the kingdom, that he commanded these bondservants, to whom he gave the silver, to be summoned to him, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> he might know what they had made by trading.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the first came before him, saying, Lord, your two-hundred denarius coin has </font><i><font color=#FF0000>been</font></i><font color=#FF0000> worked </font><i><font color=#FF0000>up</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to ten two-hundred denarius coins more.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said to him, Well done, you good bondservant, because you became faithful in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> least </font><i><font color=#FF0000>matters</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, you have authority over ten cities.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the second came, saying, Your two-hundred denarius coin, Lord, has made</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> five two-hundred denarius coins.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he also said to him, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>I will</font></i><font color=#FF0000> let you become </font><i><font color=#FF0000>leader</font></i><font color=#FF0000> over five cities.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And another </font><i><font color=#FF0000>bondservant</font></i><font color=#FF0000> came, saying, Lord, behold, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>here is</font></i><font color=#FF0000> your two-hundred denarius coin, which I had laid up in a handkerchief;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I feared you, because you are an austere man. You lift up </font><i><font color=#FF0000>from</font></i><font color=#FF0000> what you did not lay down and reap what you did not sow.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But he says to him, I will judge you out of your own mouth, you evil bondservant. You knew that I am an austere man, lifting up </font><i><font color=#FF0000>from</font></i><font color=#FF0000> what I did not lay down and reaping what I did not sow?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Then why did you not give my silver into </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> bank and when I came </font><i><font color=#FF0000>back,</font></i><font color=#FF0000> I might have appropriated it with interest?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he said to those standing by, Take away from him the two-hundred denarius coin and give </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to him who has the ten two-hundred denarius coins.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And they said to him, Lord, he has ten two-hundred denarius coins. </font><i><font color=#FF0000>Why?</font></i>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> that to everyone who has will be given, but from him who has not, even what he has will be taken away from him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>However these, my enemies, that did not wish that I should reign over them, lead </font><i><font color=#FF0000>them</font></i><font color=#FF0000> here and slaughter </font><i><font color=#FF0000>them</font></i><font color=#FF0000> in front of me.</font> <font color=#808080>{Week of the Crucifixion.)</font>Luke 19:28 And when he had spoken these things, he traveled on in front of them, going up to Jerusalem.'],
   ['And it happened, when he drew near to Bethphage and Bethany, toward the mountain that is called Olives, he sent two of the disciples,'],
   ['saying,<font color=#FF0000> Go your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> way into the village before </font><i><font color=#FF0000>me</font></i><font color=#FF0000>; in which as you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> travel in, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will find a colt tied, on which</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>no man </font><i><font color=#FF0000>has </font></i><font color=#FF0000>sat at anytime. Loose and lead him </font><i><font color=#FF0000>here</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And if anyone asks you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, Why do you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> loose him? You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will say to him thus, The Lord has need of him.</font>'],
   ['And those who were sent went away and found just-as he had said to them.'],
   ['And as they loosed the colt, its lords said to them, Why do you* loose the colt?'],
   ['And they said, The Lord has need of it.'],
   ['And they lead him to Jesus and having tossed their garments upon the colt, they mounted Jesus upon it.'],
   ['And as he traveled, they spread their garments in the road.'],
   ['Now as he was already drawing near, even to the slope of the Mountain of Olives, the whole crowd of the disciples began rejoicing, and to praise God with a loud voice concerning all the miracles which they had seen;'],
   ['saying, The King that is coming in the name of the Lord is blessed; peace in heaven and glory in the highest.'],
   ['And some of the Pharisees from the crowd said to him, Teacher, rebuke your disciples.'],
   ['And answering, he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> that if these </font><i><font color=#FF0000>disciples</font></i><font color=#FF0000> are silent, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>then</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the stones will cry out.</font>'],
   ['And when he drew near, he saw the city and wept over it,'],
   ['saying,<font color=#FF0000> If you had known in this day, even you, for-sure, the things </font><i><font color=#FF0000>which are</font></i><font color=#FF0000> for your peace! But now they are hid from your eyes.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because the days will come upon you, when your enemies will put a military-barrier around you and surround you and crowd you on every side,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and will level you to the bedrock and your children with you, and they will not leave in you one stone upon </font><i><font color=#FF0000>another</font></i><font color=#FF0000> stone, because you did not know the time of your visitation.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 11:12-18 &amp; Mt 21:18, 19, 12, 13 &amp; Lk 19:45-48 Road from Bethany to Jerusalem Mon.</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And he entered into the temple and began to cast out those who were selling and buying in it,'],
   ['saying to them, <font color=#FF0000>&lsquo;It has been written, my house will be a house of prayer, but you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have made</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> it a den of robbers.&rsquo;</font><font color=#FF0000> </font><font color=#808080>{Is. 56:7 &amp; Jer. 7:11}</font>'],
   ['And he was teaching daily in the temple. But the high-priests and the scribes and the foremost ones of the people sought to destroy him.'],
   ['And they could not find what they might do; for* the people all hung on every word, listening to him.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Lk 19:30- Greek: no one from men.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:20
   ['And it happened on one of those days, while he is teaching the people in the temple and proclaiming the good-news, the priests and the scribes, with the elders stood up;'],
   ['and they spoke saying to him, Tell us, by what authority are you doing these things? Or who is he who gave you this authority?'],
   ['And answering, he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> I will also ask you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> one</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>question and tell me.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The immersion</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> of John, was it from heaven or from men?</font>'],
   ['And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we should say, From heaven; he will say, Then why did you* not believe him?'],
   ['But if we say, From men; all the people will stone us; for* they have confidence that John was a prophet.'],
   ['And they answered that they did not know where it was from.'],
   ['And Jesus said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Neither do I tell you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> by what authority I am doing these things.</font>'],
   ['And he began to speak to the people this parable:<font color=#FF0000> A man planted a vineyard and rented it to farmers and went abroad for a considerable time.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And in the </font><i><font color=#FF0000>harvest</font></i><font color=#FF0000> season he sent to the farmers a bondservant, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> they might give to him from the fruit of the vineyard, but the farmers whipped him and sent him away empty </font><i><font color=#FF0000>handed</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he sent yet another bondservant and they also whipped and dishonored him and sent him away empty</font>.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he sent yet a third and they also traumatized him and cast him forth.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the lord of the vineyard said, What should I do? I will send my beloved son; perchance seeing </font><i><font color=#FF0000>him</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, they will revere him.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But when the farmers saw him, they reasoned among themselves, saying, This is the heir. Come-here. We should kill him, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the inheritance may become ours.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And they cast him forth outside the vineyard and killed him. Therefore what will the lord of the vineyard do to them?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He will come and destroy these farmers and will give the vineyard to others.</font> And when they heard it, they said, Let it not happen!'],
   ['But he looked on them and said, <font color=#FF0000>Then</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> what is this that is written, &lsquo;The stone which the builders rejected</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, this one has become the head of the corner?&rsquo;</font><font color=#FF0000> </font><font color=#808080>{Ps. 118:22}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Everyone who falls upon that stone will be shattered, but </font><i><font color=#FF0000>upon</font></i><font color=#FF0000> whomever it falls, it will smash him.</font>'],
   ['And the high-priests and the scribes sought to put hands upon him in that same hour and they feared; for* they knew that he spoke this parable to them.'],
   ['And they having observed him, sent forth agents, who pretended to be righteous, that* they might grab him in his speech, *that* they might give him to the rule and to the authority of the governor.'],
   ['And they asked him, saying, Teacher, we know that you say and teach uprightly and do not accept the countenance of men, but in truth, are teaching the way of God.'],
   ['Is it legal for us to give tax to Caesar or not?'],
   ['But he perceived their craftiness and said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Why do you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> test me?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Show me a denarius. Whose image and inscription has it?</font> And answering, they said, Caesar&rsquo;s.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Now-then, give to Caesar the things that are Caesar&rsquo;s and to God the things that are God&rsquo;s.</font>'],
   ['And they were not strong-enough to grab his saying before the people and they marveled at his answer and were silent.'],
   ['And some of the Sadducees came to him, those who contradict that there is a resurrection;'],
   ['and they asked him, saying, Teacher, Moses wrote to us, that* if anyone&rsquo;s brother dies, who had a wife and he should die childless, his brother should take the wife and should raise* up seed to his brother. <font color=#808080>{Deut. 25:5}</font>'],
   ['Therefore there were seven brethren and the first took a wife and died childless;'],
   ['and the second took the woman and he died childless;'],
   ['and the third took her, and likewise* the seven also left no children and died.'],
   ['Later the woman also died.'],
   ['Therefore in the resurrection whose wife of them does she become? For* the seven had her as wife.'],
   ['And Jesus answering, said to them, <font color=#FF0000>The sons of this world marry and are betrothed.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But those who are deemed worthy to obtain that world and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry, nor are they betrothed,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> neither are they able to die any more; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> they are equal to the messengers, and are sons of God, being sons of the resurrection.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But that the dead do arise, even Moses divulged in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the place concerning</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the bush, as he calls the Lord, the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob.</font><font color=#FF0000> </font><font color=#808080>{Ex. 3:6}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Now he is not the God of the dead, but of the living; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> all live to him.</font>'],
   ['And some of the scribes answering said, Teacher, you have said well.'],
   ['But they did not dare any more to ask him anything.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> How </font><i><font color=#FF0000>is it that</font></i><font color=#FF0000> they say the Christ is David&rsquo;s son?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And David himself says in the book of Psalms, &lsquo;The Lord said to my Lord, You sit at my right </font><i><font color=#FF0000>hand</font></i><font color=#FF0000>,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>until I should place your enemies </font><i><font color=#FF0000>under the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> footstool of your feet.</font> <font color=#808080>{Ps. 110:1}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore David calls him Lord and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>so</font></i><font color=#FF0000> how is he his son?</font>'],
   ['And he said to his disciples with all the people hearing this,'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Take-heed of the scribes, who wish to walk in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>long</font></i><font color=#FF0000> robes and love greetings in the marketplaces and foremost seats in the synagogues and foremost-places in the suppers;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>who are devouring widow&rsquo;s houses and are praying long </font><i><font color=#FF0000>prayers</font></i><font color=#FF0000> for a pretext. These will receive even-more condemnation.</font> <font color=#808080></font>'],
  ],
  [ // 42:21
   ['And he looked up and saw the rich men casting their gifts into the treasury.'],
   ['And he also saw a certain poor widow casting two bronze-coins in there.'],
   ['And he said,<font color=#FF0000> Truly I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, This poor widow cast in more-than they all.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> all these cast into the gifts of God out of what is abounding to them, but she cast in out of her deficit, all the livelihood that she had.</font><font color=#808080></font> {Lk 21:5-24 &amp; Mt 24:1-28 &amp; Mk 13:1-23 Destruction of Jerusalem in 70 AD. See also: Lk 19:41-44 &amp; Lk 23:28-31.}'],
   ['And as some spoke about the temple, how it was adorned with good stones and votive-offerings, he said,'],
   ['<i><font color=#FF0000>As for</font></i><font color=#FF0000> these things which you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are viewing, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> days will come, in which </font><i><font color=#FF0000>one</font></i><font color=#FF0000> stone will not be left here upon </font><i><font color=#FF0000>another</font></i><font color=#FF0000> stone, that will not be torn-down.</font>'],
   ['And they asked him, saying, Therefore teacher, when will these things be? And what will be the sign whenever these things are about to happen?'],
   ['And he said, <font color=#FF0000>Beware you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are not misled; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> many will come in my name, saying, I am </font><i><font color=#FF0000>he</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, and, The time has drawn near. Therefore you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> do not go after them.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And whenever you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font> <font color=#FF0000>hear of wars and unrest, do not be terrified; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> these things must happen first, but the end </font><i><font color=#FF0000>is</font></i><font color=#FF0000> not immediately </font><i><font color=#FF0000>here</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['Then he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Nation will arise against nation and kingdom against kingdom;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and there will be great earthquakes in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>different</font></i><font color=#FF0000> places and famines and plagues. There will be both terrors and great signs from heaven.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But before all these things, they will lay their hands upon you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> and will persecute you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, giving you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> up to the synagogues and prisons, leading </font><i><font color=#FF0000>you</font></i><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> before kings and governors because of my name.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But it will transpire for you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> into a testimony.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore settle it into your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hearts, not to meditate beforehand how to make a</font> <font color=#FF0000>defense.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I will give you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a mouth and wisdom, which all who lay in opposition to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will not be </font>able to withstand nor to speak against.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will be given up even by parents and brethren and relatives and friends, and they will put to death </font><i><font color=#FF0000>some</font></i><font color=#FF0000> out of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will be hated by all men because of my name.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And a hair out of your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> head may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> perish.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will procure your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> souls in your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> endurance.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But whenever you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behold Jerusalem surrounded by encamped armies, then know that her desolation has drawn near.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Then let those who are in Judea escape to the mountains, and let those who are in the midst of her vacate, and do not let those who are in the country enter in it.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because these are days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing in those days! For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a great calamity will be upon the land and wrath among this people.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And they will fall by the edge of the sword and will be captured into all the nations and Jerusalem will be trampled on by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles should be fulfilled.</font><font color=#808080> {Lk 21:25-28 &amp; Mt 24:29-51 &amp; Mk 13:24-37 &amp; 2Th 1:7-9 Second Coming}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And there will be signs in the sun and moon and stars, and dismay of nations upon the earth, in perplexity </font><i><font color=#FF0000>from</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the noise of the sea and the billows;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>men</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>passing-out from fear and expectation of the things which are coming on the inhabited-earth; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the powers of the heavens will</font> <font color=#FF0000>be shaken.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And then they will see the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But when these things are beginning to happen, stand-erect and lift up your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> heads, because your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> redemption is drawing near</font>.<font color=#808080></font> {Lk 21:29-33 &amp; Mt 24:32-35 &amp; Mk 13:28-31 Destruction of Jerusalem AD 70}'],
   ['And he spoke to them a parable:<font color=#FF0000> Behold the fig tree and all the trees.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Whenever they already cast forth </font><i><font color=#FF0000>leaves</font></i><font color=#FF0000>, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> know from looking </font><i><font color=#FF0000>at them</font></i><font color=#FF0000> yourselves that the summer is already near.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>So also you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, whenever you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behold these things happening, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> know that the kingdom of God is near.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Assuredly I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, This generation may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> pass away, until all things should happen.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The heaven and the earth will pass away, but my words may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> pass away.</font> <font color=#808080>{Lk 21:34-36 &amp; Mt 24:36-44 &amp; Mk 13:32-37 Second Coming}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But take-heed to yourselves, lest your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hearts might be burdened with a hangover and drunkenness and anxieties of everyday life and that day might suddenly stand upon you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> it will come like a snare upon all those sitting upon the face of all the earth.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> watch in every season, beseeching, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> might be deemed worthy to escape all the things which are about to happen and to stand in front of the Son of Man.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 11:19-26 &amp; Mt 21:20-22 &amp; Lk 21:37-38 Road from Bethany to Jerusalem Tues.</font><font color=#808080>}</font><font color=#808080></font>'],
   ['And every day he was teaching in the temple, and every night he went out and camped in the mountain that is called Olives.'],
   ['And all the people came at early-morning to hear him in the temple. <font color=#808080> {Mk 14:1-2 &amp; Mt 26:1-5 &amp; Lk 22:1-2 mountain Olives, Bethany, Jerusalem, Tues. Evening, Wed. for the Jews}</font>'],
  ],
  [ // 42:22
   ['Now the feast of unleavened bread drew near, which is called the Passover.'],
   ['And the high-priests and the scribes sought how they might assassinate him; for* they feared the people.<font color=#808080> {Mk 14:10-11 &amp; Mt 26:14-16 &amp; Lk 22:3-6 &amp; Jn 12:2-8}</font>'],
   ['And the Adversary entered into Judas who is surnamed Iscariot, being out of the number of the twelve.'],
   ['And he went away and spoke with the high-priests and captains, how he might give him to them.'],
   ['And they rejoiced and covenanted to give him silver.'],
   ['And he professed agreement and sought opportunity to give him up to them without the crowd.<font color=#808080> {Mk 14:12-17 &amp; Mt 26:17-20 &amp; Lk 22:7-18, 24-30 Bethany to Jerusalem Thurs. Evening</font><font color=#808080>}</font><font color=#808080></font>'],
   ['And the day of unleavened bread came in which the Passover must be sacrificed.'],
   ['And he sent Peter and John, saying, <font color=#FF0000>Go and prepare the Passover for us, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> we may eat.</font>'],
   ['And they said to him, Where do you will that we prepare it?'],
   ['And he said to them <font color=#FF0000>Behold, when you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have entered into the city, a man bearing a pitcher of water will meet you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> there; follow him into the house where he goes.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will say to the householder, The Teacher says to you, Where is the guestroom, where I may eat the Passover with my disciples?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he will show you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> a large furnished upper room. Prepare </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> there.</font>'],
   ['And they went and found just-as he had said to them and they prepared the Passover.'],
   ['And when the hour came, he leaned-back and the twelve apostles with him.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> I have desired, with </font><i><font color=#FF0000>a great</font></i><font color=#FF0000> desire, to eat this Passover with you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> before I suffer;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, I may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> eat from it anymore, until it should be fulfilled in the kingdom of God.</font>'],
   ['And he accepted a cup and when he had given-thanks, he said,<font color=#FF0000> Take this and divide it among yourselves.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, I may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> drink from the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of God should come.</font> <font color=#808080>{Mk 14:22-25 &amp; Mt 26:26-29 &amp; Lk 22:19-20, 1Cor: 11:23-26}</font>'],
   ['And he took bread and when he had given-thanks, he broke it and gave to them, saying, <font color=#FF0000>This is my body which is given on your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behalf. Practice this in my remembrance.</font>'],
   ['And likewise* he took the cup after the supper, saying, <font color=#FF0000>This cup is the </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#FF0000> new covenant</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in my blood, which is poured out on your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behalf.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 14:18-21, 27-31 &amp; Mt 26:21-25, 31-35 &amp; Lk 22:21-23, 31-38 &amp; Jn 13:21-38}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>However behold, the hand of him who is giving me up is with me at the table.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And the Son of Man indeed is going, as it has been determined; however woe to that man through whom he is given up!</font>'],
   ['And they began to debate together with themselves, which out of them was about to do this thing.'],
   ['And there was also contention among them, which of them is thought to be the greater.'],
   ['And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>The kings of the Gentiles have lordship over them, and those who have authority over them are called benefactors.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> </font><i><font color=#FF0000>will</font></i><font color=#FF0000> not </font><i><font color=#FF0000>be</font></i><font color=#FF0000> so, but he who is the greater among you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, let him become like the younger, and he who is leader, as he who is serving.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> which is greater, he who reclines </font><i><font color=#FF0000>at the meal</font></i><font color=#FF0000> or he who is serving? Is </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> not he who reclines? But I am in your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> midst like he who serves.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are those who have remained with me in my temptations;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and I covenant to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, just-as my father covenanted to me a kingdom,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may eat and may drink upon my table in my kingdom, and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will sit upon thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.</font>'],
   ['And the Lord said, <font color=#FF0000>Simon, Simon, behold, the Adversary asked for you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, to sift </font><i><font color=#FF0000>you</font></i><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> like wheat.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But I besought concerning you, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> your faith may not fail, and when you have turned again, establish your brethren.</font>'],
   ['And he said to him, Lord, I am ready to go with you both to prison and to death.'],
   ['And he said,<font color=#FF0000> I tell you, Peter, the rooster may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> crow today, before you will deny knowing me three times.</font>'],
   ['And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>When I sent you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> forth without money-bag and knapsack and shoes, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> did not lack anything, did you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>?</font> And they said, Nothing.'],
   ['Therefore he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> But now, he who has a money-bag, let him take it and likewise a knapsack, and he who has no sword, let him sell his garment and buy one.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>For</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> that this still must be accomplished in me which has been written, &lsquo;And he was counted with the lawless; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> the things concerning me </font><i><font color=#FF0000>must</font></i><font color=#FF0000> have an end.</font>&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 53:12}</font>'],
   ['And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> It is sufficient.</font><font color=#808080></font> {Mk 14:26, 32-42 &amp; Mt 26:30, 36-46 &amp; Lk 22:39-46 &amp; Jn 18:1 Garden between Stream of Kidron and Mountain of Olives, Late Thurs. night}'],
   ['And he came out and went, according to his custom, to the Mountain of Olives, and his disciples also followed him.'],
   ['And when he was at the place, he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Pray that you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> do not enter into temptation.</font>'],
   ['And he drew away from them approximately a stone&rsquo;s throw, and placing himself on his knees and he prayed,'],
   ['saying, <font color=#FF0000>Father, if you are willing, carry this cup away from me, but not my will, but yours, be done.</font>'],
   ['And a messenger from heaven appeared to him, strengthening him.'],
   ['And being in agony he prayed more intensely, and his sweat became like thick drops of blood going down upon the soil.'],
   ['And when he rose* up from his prayer, he came to the disciples and found that they had fallen-asleep from sorrow,'],
   ['and said to them, <font color=#FF0000>Why are you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> sleeping? Rise</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> up and pray, that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may not enter into temptation.</font>'],
   ['While he still spoke, behold a crowd and he who was called Judas, one of the twelve, went before them, and he drew near to Jesus to kiss him.'],
   ['But Jesus said to him, <font color=#FF0000>Judas, are you giving up the Son of Man with a kiss?</font>'],
   ['And when those who were around him saw what will be coming, they said to him, Lord, shall we strike with the sword?'],
   ['And a certain one out of them struck the bondservant of the high-priest and took off his right ear.'],
   ['But answering, Jesus said, <font color=#FF0000>Permit this. </font>And he touched his ear and healed him.'],
   ['And Jesus said to the high-priests and captains of the temple and elders, that had come against him, <font color=#FF0000>Have you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> come out with swords and clubs, like against a robber?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>When I was with you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> daily in the temple, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> did not stretch out your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hands against me, but this is your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hour and the authority of darkness</font>.<font color=#808080> {Mk 14:66-72 &amp; Mt 26:69-75 &amp; Lk 22:54-62</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>&amp; Jn 18:25-27</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['But taking him, they led and brought him into the high-priest&rsquo;s house. But Peter followed from afar.'],
   ['And when they had lit a fire in the middle of the courtyard and they had sat down together, Peter sat in the midst of them.'],
   ['And a certain maidservant seeing him as he sat in the light of the fire and staring at him, said, This man was also with him.'],
   ['But he denied him, saying, Woman, I do not know him.'],
   ['And after a little bit another saw him and said, You also are one out of them. But Peter said, Man, I am not.'],
   ['And after approximately a one hour interval, then a certain other stoutly affirmed, saying, Of a truth this man was also with him; for* he is a Galilean.'],
   ['But Peter said, Man, I do not know what you say. And instantly, while he still spoke the rooster crowed.'],
   ['And the Lord turned and looked on Peter. And Peter was reminded the word of the Lord, how that he said to him, Before the rooster crow this day you will deny me three times.'],
   ['And he went outside and wept bitterly.<font color=#808080> {Mk 14:55-65 &amp; Mt 26:59-68 &amp; Lk 22:63-65</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And the men who held Jesus mocked him while whipping him.'],
   ['And having covered him, they were beating his face, and were asking him, saying, Prophesy. Who is it who struck you?'],
   ['And they spoke many other things to him, blaspheming. <font color=#808080>{Mk 15:1 &amp; Mt 27:1-2 Lk 22:66-23:1 &amp; Jn 18:28 Jerusalem early Friday morning.}</font>'],
   ['And as it became day, the eldership of the people was gathered together, both high-priests and scribes, and they led him away into their council, saying,'],
   ['If you are the Christ, tell us. But he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>If I tell you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> believe;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and if I also ask, you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> answer or release </font><i><font color=#FF0000>me</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>From hereafter, the Son of Man will be seated at </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> right </font><i><font color=#FF0000>hand</font></i><font color=#FF0000> of the power of God.</font>'],
   ['And they all said, Then<font color=#FF0000>*</font> are you the Son of God? And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>You</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are saying that I am.</font>'],
   ['And they said, Why do we still have need of testimony? For* we ourselves have heard from his own mouth.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Lk 22:20 See Appendix under Covenant.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 42:23
   ['And the whole crowd of them stood up and led him before Pilate.<font color=#808080> {Mk 15:2-5 &amp; Mt 27:11-14 &amp; Lk 23:2-5 &amp; Jn 18:28-38 Jerusalem early Friday morning</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And they began to accuse him, saying, We found this man perverting the nation and forbidding to give tribute to Caesar and saying that he himself is Christ a king.'],
   ['And Pilate asked him, saying, Are you the King of the Jews? And answering him, he said,<font color=#FF0000> You say </font><i><font color=#FF0000>correctly</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['And Pilate said to the high-priests and the crowds, I am finding no crime in this man.'],
   ['But they were insisting, saying, He is stirring up the people, teaching throughout all of Judea and beginning from Galilee even to here.<font color=#808080> {Lk 23:6-12 Jerusalem early Friday morning</font><font color=#808080>}</font><font color=#808080></font>'],
   ['But when Pilate heard it, he asked if the man was a Galilean.'],
   ['And when he recognized that he is out of Herod&rsquo;s authority, he sent him back to Herod, who himself was also in Jerusalem in these days.'],
   ['Now when Herod saw Jesus, he rejoiced exceedingly; for* he was wishing for a considerable time to see him, because of the many things which he had heard concerning him, and he hoped to see some sign done by him.'],
   ['And he asked him questions with considerable words, but he answered him nothing.'],
   ['And the high-priests and the scribes stood, intensely accusing him.'],
   ['And Herod with his soldiers having scorned and having mocked him and dressed him in bright apparel sent him back to Pilate.'],
   ['And Pilate and Herod became friends with one another in that same day; for* they were formerly at enmity between themselves.'],
   ['And Pilate called together the high-priests and the rulers and the people,'],
   ['and said to them, You* brought this man to me, as one turning away the people to riot and behold, I have examined him before you*, and found no crime in this man of which you* accuse a crime against him.'],
   ['But even Herod found nothing. For* he sent him back to you*, and behold, nothing worthy of death has been practiced by him.'],
   ['Therefore I will discipline him and release him.'],
   ['But, he had to release to them one prisoner at the feast by necessity.'],
   ['But they cried out altogether, saying, Take away this man and release Barabbas to us.'],
   ['<i>He was one</i> who was cast into prison because of a certain riot which happened in the city and for murder.'],
   ['Therefore Pilate shouted to them again, wishing to release Jesus.'],
   ['But they shouted out, saying, Crucify him! Crucify him!'],
   ['And he said to them the third time, For* what evil has this man done? I have found no crime worthy of death in him; therefore I will discipline him and release him.'],
   ['But they were urgently asking with loud voices, that he might be crucified. And their voices and those of the high-priests prevailed.'],
   ['But Pilate decided their request was to happen.'],
   ['And he released to them he who had been cast into the prison because of riot and murder, whom they asked for, but Jesus he gave up to their will.<font color=#808080></font> {Mk 15:20-23 &amp; Mt 27:31-34 &amp; Lk 23:26-33 &amp; Jn 19:17 Road to the Cross, Friday morning<font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And when they led him away, they grabbed a certain person named Simon from Cyrene, coming from the rural area and laid on him the cross, to carry it behind Jesus.'],
   ['And a great crowd of the people and of women were also following him. They were grieving and mourning for him.'],
   ['But Jesus turning to them said,<font color=#FF0000> Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, however weep for yourselves and for your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> children.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because behold, the days are coming, in which they will say, The barren are fortunate and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> wombs that did not give-birth and the breasts that did not nurse.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Then they will begin to say to the mountains, Fall upon us, and to the hills, Cover us.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because if they are doing these things in the green tree, what might happen in the dry?</font>'],
   ['And two others, also criminals, were led with him to be taken away.<font color=#808080> {Mk 15:24-32 &amp; Mt 27:35-44 &amp; Lk 23:33-43 &amp; Jn 19:18-27 9:00 until Noon, Friday</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And when they came upon the place which is called The Skull, they crucified him and the criminals there, one at the right and the other at the left.'],
   ['And Jesus said, <font color=#FF0000>Father, forgive them; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> they do not know what they are doing</font>. And they cast lots, dividing his garments among them.'],
   ['And the people stood viewing and the rulers with them also ridiculed him, saying, He saved others; let him save himself, if this is the Christ of God, his chosen.'],
   ['And the soldiers also mocked him, coming to him and offering him vinegar,'],
   ['and saying, If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself.'],
   ['And an inscription was also over him written in the alphabet of Greek and Latin and Hebrew, THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.'],
   ['And one of the criminals who hung there, blasphemed him, saying, If you are the Christ save yourself and us!'],
   ['But the other answering, rebuked him, saying, Do you not fear even God, because you are in the same condemnation?'],
   ['And we indeed suffer righteously; for* we are receiving worthy payment of what we practiced, but this man has practiced nothing improper.'],
   ['And he said, Jesus, remember me Lord, whenever you come in your kingdom.'],
   ['And he said to him,<font color=#FF0000> Assuredly I say to you. Today you will be with me in Paradise.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 15:34 &amp; Mt 27:45 &amp; Lk 23:44 around Noon.}</font>'],
   ['And it was approximately the sixth hour and there became darkness upon the whole earth until the ninth hour. <font color=#808080>{Mk 15:34-41 &amp; Mt 27:46-56 &amp; Lk 23:45-49 &amp; Jn 19:28-30 around 5:00 PM}</font>'],
   ['And the sun was darkened and the curtain of the temple was split-apart in the middle.'],
   ['And Jesus having shouted with a loud voice, said, <font color=#FF0000>Father, I will intrust my spirit into your hands.</font> And having said these things, he expired.'],
   ['And when the centurion saw what had happened, he glorified God, saying, This was really a righteous man.'],
   ['And all the crowds that came together upon this scene, viewing the things that had happened, returned beating their chest.'],
   ['And all his acquaintances and the women who followed from Galilee with him, stood from afar, seeing these things.<font color=#808080> {Mk 15:42-47 &amp; Mt 27:57-66 &amp; Lk 23:50-56 &amp; Jn 19:31-42 Before The Sabbath.</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And behold, a man named Joseph, who is* a counselor, a good and righteous man'],
   ['(he had not concurred to their counsel and practice), a man of Arimathaea, a city of the Jews, who himself was also waiting for the kingdom of God.'],
   ['This man having gone to Pilate, asked for the body of Jesus.'],
   ['And he took it down and entwined it in a linen cloth and laid it in a hewn out tomb, where a man had not yet laid.'],
   ['And it was the day of the Preparation and the Sabbath was dawning.'],
   ['And the women, who had come with him out of Galilee, followed after and saw the tomb and how his body was laid.'],
   ['And they returned and prepared spices and perfumes. And on the Sabbath they relaxed according to the commandment. <font color=#808080> {Mk 16:1-8 &amp; Mt 28:1-8 &amp; Lk 24:1-8, 12 &amp; Jn 20:1-10 Dawn and very early Sunday</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
  ],
  [ // 42:24
   ['But on the first day of the week, from the deep fog of early-morning, they and some others with them came to the tomb, bringing the spices which they had prepared.'],
   ['And they found the stone rolled away from the tomb.'],
   ['And they entered in and did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.'],
   ['And it happened, while they were perplexed concerning this, behold, two men stood by them in flashing white apparel;'],
   ['and as they became fearful and bowing their faces down to the earth, they said to them, Why are you* seeking the living with the dead?'],
   ['He is not here, but has arisen. Do you<i>*</i> remember how he spoke to you* when he was still in Galilee,'],
   ['saying that the Son of Man must be given up into the hands of sinful men and to be crucified and to rise* up in the third day?'],
   ['And they remembered his words.<font color=#808080> {Mk 16:9-11 &amp; Mt 28:9-10 &amp; Lk 24:9-11 &amp; Jn 20:11-18}</font>'],
   ['And they returned from the tomb and reported all these things to the eleven and to all the rest.'],
   ['Now they were Mary Magdalene and Joanna and Mary the mother of James and the rest of the women with them who told these things to the apostles.'],
   ['And their words appeared in their sight like nonsense, and they disbelieved them.'],
   ['But Peter stood up and ran to the tomb, and stooping down and looking in, he sees only the linen-strips lying alone, and he went away to his home, marveling at what had happened.<font color=#808080> {Mk 16:12-13 &amp; Lk 24:13-35 &amp; 1Cor: 15:5 Sunday Afternoon</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And behold, two out of them were going that same day to a village named Emmaus, which was sixty furlongs distant from Jerusalem.'],
   ['And they conversed with each other concerning all these things which had befell them.'],
   ['And it happened, while they conversed and debated together, that Jesus himself drew near and traveled together with them.'],
   ['But their eyes were held-fast so as not to recognize him.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> What words </font><i><font color=#FF0000>are</font></i><font color=#FF0000> these which you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are exchanging </font><i><font color=#FF0000>back and forth</font></i><font color=#FF0000> with one another, as you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are walking? and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have a gloomy face, </font><i><font color=#FF0000>why</font></i><font color=#FF0000>?</font>'],
   ['And one whose name was Cleopas answering, said to him, Are you sojourning alone in Jerusalem and do not know the things that have happened in her in these days?'],
   ['And he said to them, <font color=#FF0000>What things?</font> And they said to him, The things concerning Jesus the Nazarene, who was a prophet mighty in works and word before God and all the people;'],
   ['and how the high-priests and our rulers gave him up to be condemned to death and crucified him.'],
   ['But we were hoping he was the one who was about to redeem Israel. But then with all these things, today is bringing the third day since these things happened.'],
   ['But some women out of us also astonished us, having been at the tomb in the early-morning,'],
   ['and having not found his body, they came, saying, that they had also seen a vision of messengers, who said that he was alive.'],
   ['And some of those who were with us, went to the tomb and also found it just-as the women had said, but they did not see him.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> O </font><i><font color=#FF0000>you</font></i><i><font color=#FF0000>*</font></i><font color=#FF0000> foolish </font><i><font color=#FF0000>ones</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and slow of heart to believe in all that the</font> <font color=#FF0000>prophets have spoken!</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Was it not essential for the Christ to suffer these things and to enter into his glory?</font>'],
   ['And beginning from Moses and from all the prophets, he clarified for them in all the Scriptures the things concerning himself.'],
   ['And they drew near to the village, where they were going and he made like he was going farther.'],
   ['And they constrained him, saying, Abide with us, because it is toward dusk and the day is far-spent. And he entered in to abide with them.'],
   ['And it happened, when he had reclined with them at the table, he took the bread and gave-thanks and breaking it he gave to them.'],
   ['And their eyes were opened and they recognized him, and he disappeared from them.'],
   ['And they said to one another, Were our hearts not burning inside us, while he spoke to us on the road, and while he opened the Scriptures to us?'],
   ['And that same hour they stood up and returned to Jerusalem and found the eleven and those who were accumulated together with them,'],
   ['saying, The Lord has really arose and has appeared to Simon.'],
   ['And they described the things that happened on the road and how he was known by them in the breaking of the bread.<font color=#808080></font> {Mk 16:14 &amp; Lk 24:36-43 &amp; Jn 20:19-25 Sunday Evening<font color=#808080>}</font><font color=#808080></font>'],
   ['And as they spoke these things, Jesus stood in the midst of them and says to them, <font color=#FF0000>Peace </font><i><font color=#FF0000>be</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['But they became terrified and fearful and thought that they had viewed a spirit.'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Why are you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> disturbed? And why do </font>questions come up in your<font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> hearts?</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>See my hands and my feet, that it is I myself. Touch me and see, because a spirit does not have flesh and bones, like you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> view me having.</font>'],
   ['And when he had said this, he showed them his hands and his feet.'],
   ['And<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>still disbelieving this from joy and marveling; he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Do you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have anything edible here?</font>'],
   ['And they gave part of a broiled fish to him and part of the honeycomb.'],
   ['And he took and ate it before them.<font color=#808080> {Lk 24:44-49 &amp; Acts 1:3-8 &amp; 1Cor: 15:7 Jerusalem</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> These are the words which I spoke to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, while I was still with you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, that all things must be fulfilled, which are written in the Law of Moses and the prophets and the Psalms, concerning me.</font>'],
   ['Then he opened their mind, that they might understand the Scriptures. <font color=#808080>{Mk 16:15-18 &amp; Mt 28:18-20 &amp; Lk 24:46-47 Mountain in Galilee; The Great Commission.}</font>'],
   ['And he said to them,<font color=#FF0000> Thus it has been written, that the Christ must suffer and rise</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> up from the dead in the third day; </font><font color=#808080>{Isa 53:5?}</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and that repentance and forgiveness of sins should be preached in his name to all the nations, beginning from Jerusalem.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> are witnesses of these things.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And behold, I am sending the promise of my Father upon you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, but you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> stick-around in the city of Jerusalem, until you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> should be clothed with power from on high.</font><font color=#808080> {Mk 16:19-20 &amp; Lk 24:50-53 &amp; Acts 1:9-12 Olivet, between Jerusalem and Bethany</font><font color=#808080>}</font>'],
   ['And he led them outside until they were in Bethany and he lifted up his hands and blessed them.'],
   ['And it happened, while he blessed them, he stood away from them and was brought up into heaven.'],
   ['And they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy'],
   ['and they were always in the temple, praising and thanking God. Amen.<font color=#808080> {Lk 24:51 i.e. They were in shock.}</font>'],
  ],
