   ['But death reigned from Adam till Moses, even over those who had not sinned in the likeness of the transgression of Adam, who is a pattern of the future one.'],
   ['But not like the trespass, so also is the gift*. For* if the many died by the trespass of the one, much more did the grace of God and the gift by the grace of the one man, Jesus the Christ, abound to the many.'],
   ['And the gift is not through one who sinned; for* indeed the judgment came from one to condemnation, but the gift* came from many trespasses to an act of righteousness.'],
   ['For* if, by the trespass of the one, death reigned through the one; much more they, who are receiving the abundance of the grace and of the gift of righteousness, will reign in life through the one, who is Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['Then* consequently, as through one trespass the judgment came to all men to condemnation; so through one act of righteousness the gift also came to all men to justification of life.'],
   ['For* as through the one man&rsquo;s disobedience* the many were designated as sinners, so also through the obedience of the one the many will be designated as righteous.'],
   ['And the law entered in besides, that* the trespass might increase, but where sin increased, grace over abounded;'],
   ['that*, as sin reigned in death, so grace might also reign through righteousness to everlasting life through Jesus the Christ our Lord. '],
