   ['For* he says to Moses, &lsquo;I will have mercy on whomever I have mercy and I will have pity on whomever I have pity.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ex. 33:19}</font>'],
   ['Then* consequently, it is not of him who wills, nor of him who runs, but of he who has mercy&ndash; God.'],
   ['For* the Scripture says to Pharaoh, &lsquo;I have lifted you up *for this same thing, *that I might show in you my power and *that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ex. 9:16}</font>'],
   ['Then* consequently, he has mercy on whom he wills and he hardens whom he wills.'],
   ['Therefore you will say to me, Why is he still finding-fault? For* who is withstanding his will?'],
   ['But-rather, O man, who are you who answers back against God? The molded thing will not say to him who molded it, why did you make* me so, will it?'],
   ['Or does the potter not have authority over the clay, to make* out of the same batch one vessel *for honor and another *for dishonor?'],
   ['But what if God, willing to show his wrath and to make his power known, carried us, vessels of wrath framed *for destruction, in much patience;'],
   ['and that* he might make known the riches of his glory upon vessels of mercy, which he prepared beforehand *for glory,'],
   ['<i>that is</i> us, whom he also invited, not only from the Jews, but also from the Gentiles?'],
   ['As he says also in Hosea, &lsquo;I will call those who are not my people, my people, and those not beloved, beloved.&rsquo;<font color=#808080>{Ho. 2:23}</font>'],
   ['And it will be, in the place where it was said to them, &lsquo;You* are not my people; they will be called sons of the living God there.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ho. 1:10}</font>'],
   ['Now Isaiah cries on behalf of Israel, &lsquo;If the number of the sons of Israel is like the sand of the sea, only the remnant will be saved;'],
   ['for* he is finishing and cutting-short the word in righteousness because having been cut-short, the Lord will make* the word upon the earth.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 10:22, 23}</font>'],
   ['And, as Isaiah has said before, &lsquo;If the Lord of Hosts had not left us a seed, we would have become like Sodom and would have been similar to Gomorrah.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 1:9}</font>'],
   ['Then* what shall we say? That the Gentiles, who were not pursuing righteousness, grabbed righteousness, even the righteousness from faith.'],
   ['But Israel, pursuing a law of righteousness, did not attain the law of righteousness.'],
   ['Why? Because it was not from faith, but as it was from works of the law, for* they stumbled on the stone of stumbling;'],
   ['just-as it has been written, &lsquo;Behold, I place a stone of stumbling and a rock of offense in Zion and everyone who believes on him will not be ashamed.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 8:14 &amp; 28:16}</font> '],
