  [ // 45:10
   ['Brethren, my heart&rsquo;s delight and my supplication to God on behalf of Israel, is *for their salvation.'],
   ['For* I testify of them that they have a zeal for God, but not according to full knowledge.'],
   ['For* being ignorant of God&rsquo;s righteousness and seeking to establish their own righteousness, they did not subject themselves to the righteousness of God.'],
   ['For* Christ is the end of the law *for righteousness to everyone who believes.'],
   ['For* Moses writes of the righteousness which is from the law, &lsquo;That the man who practices those things will live by them.&rsquo;<font color=#808080> {Lev. 18:5 Ezek. 20:11}</font>'],
   ['But the righteousness which is from faith says thus, &lsquo;Do not say in your heart, Who will ascend into heaven?&rsquo; (That is, to bring Christ down.)'],
   ['Or, &lsquo;Who will come down into the abyss?&rsquo; (That is, to bring Christ up from the dead.)'],
   ['But what does it say? &lsquo;The word is near you, in your mouth and in your heart.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Deut. 30:12-14?}</font> This is the word of the faith which we are preaching:'],
   ['that if you confess the Lord Jesus with your mouth and if you believe in your heart that God lifted him up from the dead, you will be saved;'],
   ['for* it is being believed with the heart toward righteousness and it is being confessed with the mouth toward salvation.'],
   ['For* the Scripture says, &lsquo;Everyone who believes on him will not be ashamed.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 28:16}</font>'],
   ['For* there is no distinction between Jew and Greek; for* the same Lord is Lord of all and is rich to all who is calling upon him;'],
