  [ // 45:11
   ['Therefore I say, God has not thrust away his people, has he? Let it not happen! For* I am also an Israelite, from the seed of Abraham, from the tribe of Benjamin.'],
   ['God did not thrust away his people which he knew beforehand. Or do you* not know what the Scripture says of Elijah? How he petitions God against Israel, saying,'],
   ['&lsquo;Lord, they have killed your prophets and have made ruins of your altars, and I am left alone and they are seeking my life.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{1Ki. 19:10,14}</font>'],
   ['But what does the divine-answer say to him? &lsquo;I have left to myself seven thousand men, who have not bowed the knee to Baal.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{1Ki. 19:18}</font>'],
   ['So also, then* in this current time there has also become a remnant according to the chosen of grace.'],
   ['But if it is by grace, it is no more from works, otherwise grace becomes grace no more. But if from works, no more is it grace; otherwise work is work no more.'],
   ['Then* what? What Israel is seeking after, this it did not obtain, but the chosen obtained it and the rest were hardened;'],
   ['just-as it has been written, &lsquo;God gave them a spirit of stupor, eyes that* they should not see and ears that* they should not hear, until this very day.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 29:10}</font>'],
   ['And David says, &lsquo;Let their table become a snare and a trap and an offense and a repayment to them.'],
