  [ // 46:5
   ['Fornication is heard literally to be among you* (and such fornication which is not even named among the Gentiles), that someone has his father&rsquo;s wife.'],
   ['And you* are arrogant and did not rather mourn, that* he who had done this work might be taken away out of your* midst.'],
   ['For* indeed, as being absent in body, but being present in spirit, I have already judged him thus who has worked this, (as though I were present),'],
   ['in the name of our Lord Jesus the Christ. When you* and my spirit are gathered together with the power of our Lord Jesus,'],
   ['to give such a one to the Adversary *for the utter-ruin of the flesh, that* the spirit might be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus.'],
   ['Your* boasting is not good. Do you* not know that a little leaven leavens the whole batch?'],
   ['Clean out the old leaven, that* you* may be a new batch, just-as you* are unleavened. For* Christ our Passover has also been sacrificed on our behalf.'],
   ['So-then we should celebrate the festival, not with old leaven, nor with the leaven of malice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.'],
   ['I have written to you* in my letter not to socialize with fornicators;'],
   ['and certainly not meaning with the fornicators of this world or with the greedy and swindlers or with idolaters; otherwise, you* are consequently* obligated to go forth out of the world.'],
   ['But now, I have written to you* not to socialize with anyone who is named a brother, if he is either a fornicator or greedy or an idolater or a reviler or a drunkard or an swindler; do not even eat with such a person.'],
   ['For* what do I even have to do with judging those who are outside? Do you* not judge those who are inside?'],
   ['But God will judge those who are outside and take away the evil man from among yourselves. '],
  ],
  [ // 46:6
   ['Do any of you* dare, having a matter of strife toward the other, go to court before the unrighteous and not before the holy-ones?'],
   ['Or do you* not know that the holy-ones will judge the world? And if the world is judged by you*, are you* unworthy of the smallest courts?'],
   ['Do you* not know that we will judge the messengers? How much more the things of everyday life?'],
   ['Therefore if you* indeed have courts concerning things of everyday life, why are you* seating those who are scorned in the congregation* as judges?'],
   ['I am saying this to shame you*. So is there not one wise person among you*? Not even one who will be able to judge between his brethren?'],
   ['But brother is going to court with brother and that before unbelievers!'],
   ['Therefore, it is indeed already a literal loss among you* that you* have lawsuits with one another. Why not rather just be wronged?'],
   ['No, but you* yourselves do wrong and defraud and you<i>*</i><i> do</i> these things to brethren.'],
   ['Or do you* not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be misled. Neither fornicators, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor perverts, nor homosexuals,'],
   ['nor the greedy, nor thieves, nor drunkards, nor revilers, nor swindlers, will inherit the kingdom of God.'],
   ['And some of you* were these, but you* were bathed, but you* were sanctified, but you* were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus and in the Spirit of our God.'],
   ['All things are legal for me, but not all things are advantageous. All things are legal for me, but I will not be brought under the authority by anything.'],
   ['Foods are for the belly and the belly is for foods, but God will do-away-with both this and these. But the body is not for fornication, but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.'],
   ['Now God both lifted up the Lord and will lift us up through his power.'],
   ['Do you* not know that your* bodies are members of Christ? Therefore should I take away the members of Christ and make* them members of a harlot? Let it not happen!'],
   ['Therefore do you* not know that he who is joined to a harlot is one body? For* he says, The two will become one flesh. <font color=#808080>{Gen. 2:24}</font>'],
   ['But he who is joined to the Lord is one spirit.'],
   ['Flee fornication. Every sin, whatever a man practices, is outside the body, but he who fornicates sins toward his own body.'],
   ['Or do you* not know that your* body is a temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you*, whom you* have from God? And you* are not your* own;'],
   ['for* you* were bought with a price. Glorify God in your* body and in your spirit which is God&rsquo;s! '],
