  [ // 46:7
   ['Now concerning the things of which you* wrote to me: it is good for a man not to touch a woman sexually.'],
   ['But, because of fornications, let each man have his own wife and let each woman have her own husband.'],
   ['Let the husband give to the wife her owed benevolence and likewise also the wife to the husband.'],
   ['The wife does not have authority over her own body, but the husband and likewise also the husband does not have authority over his own body, but the wife.'],
   ['Do not deprive one another, lest it is from agreement for a season, that* you* may occupy yourselves with fasting and with prayer and you* may come together to the same again, in order that the Adversary may not tempt you* because of your* shortage of self-control.'],
   ['But I am saying this by concession, not by commandment.'],
   ['For* I wish that all men were even as I am myself. But each man has his own gift* from God, one so and another thus.'],
   ['But I say to the unmarried and to widows, it is good for them if they remain even as I am.'],
   ['But if they do not have self-control, let them marry; for* it is better to marry than to be inflamed.'],
   ['But I command to the married, (not I, but the Lord), That the wife is not to be separated from her husband'],
   ['(but even if she is separated, she should remain unmarried or be reconciled to her husband), and that the husband is not to leave his wife.'],
   ['But to the rest I say, (not the Lord); if any brother has an unbelieving wife and she consents to dwell with him, let him not leave her.'],
   ['And if a wife who has an unbelieving husband and he consents to dwell with her, let her not leave her husband.'],
   ['For* the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the husband. Consequently, your* children were unclean, but now they are holy.'],
   ['Yet if the unbelieving spouse separates, let him separate; the brother or the sister is not enslaved in such. Now God has called us in peace.'],
   ['For* O wife, how do you know if you will save your husband? Or O husband, how do you know if you will save your wife?'],
   ['Except as God has divided to each one, as the Lord has called each, so let him walk. And so I command in all the congregations*.'],
   ['Was anyone called being circumcised? Let him not be uncircumcised. Has any been called in uncircumcision? Let him not be circumcised.'],
   ['Circumcision is nothing and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of the commandments of God.'],
   ['Let each one remain in that calling in which he was called.'],
   ['Were you called being a bondservant? Let it not be a care to you, but if you are also able to become free use it rather.'],
   ['For* he who was called in the Lord being a bondservant, is the Lord&rsquo;s freedman; likewise he who was called being free, is Christ&rsquo;s bondservant.'],
   ['You* were bought with a price; do not become bondservants of men.'],
   ['Brethren, let each one, in what he was called, abide with God in that.'],
   ['Now concerning virgins I have no commandment of the Lord, but I give my viewpoint, as one who has been shown-mercy by the Lord to be faithful.'],
   ['Therefore I suppose this to be* good because of the present necessity that is upon us; that it is good for a man to be like he is.'],
   ['Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek to be loosed. Are you loosed from a wife? Do not seek a wife.'],
   ['But even if you marry, you have not sinned, and if a virgin marries, she has not sinned. Yet such will have affliction in the flesh and I would spare you*.'],
   ['But, I say this, brethren, the time is limited, that* henceforth both those who have wives may be as though they had none;'],
   ['and those who weep, as though they did not weep, and those who rejoice, as though they did not rejoice, and those who buy, as though they did not have;'],
   ['and those who use this world, as though they did not make full use of it; for* the fashion of this world is passing away.'],
   ['But I wish for you* to be carefree. He who is unmarried is anxious for the things of the Lord, how he will please the Lord;'],
   ['but he who is married is anxious for the things of the world, how he may please his wife.'],
   ['He has been divided. The unmarried woman (also the virgin) is anxious for that which is of the Lord, that* she may be holy both in body and in spirit, but she who is married is anxious for the things of the world, how she will please her husband.'],
   ['And I say this is advantageous for yourselves*, not that* I may cast a noose upon you*, but *for what is decent and that you* may be devoted to the Lord without distraction.'],
   ['But if anyone supposes he is behaving improperly toward his virgin, if she is beyond her prime and thus it ought to happen, let him do what he wills; he is not sinning; let them marry.'],
   ['But he who stands, grounded in his heart, having no necessity, but has the authority concerning his own will and he has decided this in his own heart to keep his own virgin, he does well.'],
   ['So-then both he who betroths his own virgin does well, and he who does not betroth his own virgin is doing better.'],
   ['A wife is bound by law inasmuch time as her husband is living, but if the husband has fallen-asleep, she is free to be married to whom she wills, but only in the Lord.'],
   ['But she is fortunate if she remains so, according to my viewpoint and I think that I also have the Spirit of God. '],
  ],
  [ // 46:8
   ['Now concerning idol-sacrifices: we know that all have knowledge. Knowledge is arrogant, but love* builds up.'],
   ['But if anyone thinks to have known anything, he has known nothing yet like he ought to know;'],
   ['but if anyone loves* God, this one is known by him.'],
   ['Therefore concerning the food of idol-sacrifices, we know that an idol is nothing in the world and that there is no other God except one.'],
   ['For* if indeed there are so called gods, if in heaven or upon the earth; as there are many such gods and many such lords,'],
   ['but to us there is one God, the Father, from whom are all things and we are *for him, and one Lord, Jesus the Christ, through whom are all things and we through him.'],
   ['But that knowledge is not in all people, but some until now, with the consciousness of the idol, eat it like an idol-sacrifice, and their conscience is defiled, being weak.'],
   ['But food does not present us to God; for* neither, if we eat, do we abound? Nor, if we do not eat, are we lacking?'],
   ['But beware lest this liberty of yours* might become a stumbling block to the weak.'],
   ['For* if anyone sees you, (you who has knowledge), reclining at a table in an idol&rsquo;s sanctuary, will not his conscience, being weak, be built up, *that* he might eat idol-sacrifices?'],
   ['And the weak brother will perish on account of your knowledge, but Christ died because of him.'],
   ['And thus by sinning directly at the brethren and beating their conscience when it is weak, you* are sinning directly at Christ.'],
   ['Hence, if food is offending my brother, I should never* eat that meat forever, that* I may not offend my brother. '],
  ],
  [ // 46:9
   ['Am I not an apostle? Am I not free? Have I not seen Jesus the Christ our Lord? Are you* not my work in the Lord?'],
   ['If I am not an apostle to others, but yet I am to you*; for* you* are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.'],
   ['My defense to those who are examining me is this:'],
   ['have we no authority to eat and to drink?'],
   ['Have we no authority to lead around a wife, (a sister in the Lord), even as the rest of the apostles and the brethren of the Lord and Cephas?'],
   ['Or is it only Barnabas and I who have no authority not to work?'],
   ['Does anyone ever make war while supplying his own rations? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat from its fruit? Or who shepherds a flock and does not drink from the milk of the flock?'],
   ['I am not speaking these things according to human standards. Or is the law not also saying these things?'],
   ['For* it has been written in the Law of Moses, &lsquo;You will not muzzle a threshing bull.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Deut. 25:4}</font> There is not care only for the bulls with God, is there?'],
   ['Or does he certainly say it because of us? For* it was written because of us, that the one who is plowing ought to plow in hope and the one who is threshing ought to thresh in hope to partake of his hope.'],
   ['If we sowed spiritual things to you*, is it a great thing if we will reap your* fleshly things?'],
   ['If others are partaking of this authority over you*, do we not yet more? But we did not use this authority, but we are forbearing all things, that* we should give no hindrance to the good-news of Christ.'],
   ['Do you* not know that those who work at the sacred things, eat from the things of the temple and those who wait-upon the altar have their part with the altar?'],
   ['So, the Lord also commanded that those who are proclaiming the good-news, to live out of the good-news.'],
   ['But I used none of these things and I do not write these things that* it may become so with me; for* it would be good for me rather to die, than that* anyone should make my boasting void.'],
   ['For* if I proclaim the good-news, it is not boasting to me; for* necessity is laid upon me, but woe is to me, if I do not proclaim the good-news.'],
   ['For* if I am doing this voluntarily, I have a reward, but if I do so involuntarily, I have a stewardship entrusted to me.'],
   ['Then* what is my reward? That*, when I proclaim the good-news of the Christ, I may place the good-news before you* without cost, *that* I may not make full use of my authority in the good-news.'],
   ['For* although <font color=#808080>{F}</font> I was free from all, I enslaved myself to all, in order that I might gain all the more.'],
   ['And I became like a Jew to the Jews, in order that I might gain Jews. I became like those under the law to those who are under the law, in order that I might gain those who are under the law.'],
   ['<i>I became</i> to those who are lawless, like the lawless, (not being lawless to God, but lawful to Christ), in order that I might gain those who are lawless.'],
   ['I became like the weak to those who are weak, in order that I might gain the weak. I have become all things to all men, in order that I may certainly save some.'],
   ['And I am doing this because of the good-news, in order that I may become a fellow partner of it.'],
   ['Do you* not know that those who run in the stadium, all run, but only one receives the prize? So run that* you* may grab it.'],
   ['And everyone who struggles in the race exercises self-control in all things. Therefore they do it in order that they may receive a corruptible crown, but we an incorruptible crown.'],
   ['Now-then, I run as so, not with uncertainty. I am combating as so, not just whipping the air;'],
   ['but I am buffeting my body and enslaving it; lest somehow after having preached to others, I myself might become unapproved.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Co 9:19 I was a free </font><i><font color=#808080>man</font></i><font color=#808080> from all</font><i><font color=#808080>,</font></i><font color=#808080> I was a bondservant to all,}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 46:10
   ['Now brethren, I do not wish you* to be ignorant that our fathers were all under the cloud and all went through the sea;'],
   ['and were all immersed* into Moses in the cloud and in the sea;'],
   ['and all ate the same spiritual food;'],
   ['and all drank the same spiritual drink; for* they drank from a spiritual rock following them and the rock was Christ.'],
   ['Yet God was not delighted with most of them; for* they were overthrown in the wilderness.'],
   ['Now these things became our examples, *that* we should not be desirers of evil things, as they also lusted.'],
   ['Neither should you* become idolaters, as some of them were; as it has been written, &lsquo;The people sat down to eat and drink and rose* up to play.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ex. 32:6}</font>'],
   ['Neither should we fornicate, like some of them fornicated and twenty three thousand fell in one day.'],
   ['Nor should we test the Christ, just as some of them also tested him and perished by the serpents.'],
   ['Nor murmur, like some of them also murmured and perished by the destroyer.'],
   ['Now all these things befell them as examples, and they were written for our admonition, upon whom the ends of the ages have arrived.'],
   ['So-then he who thinks he stands, let him beware, lest he might fall!'],
   ['No temptation has taken you* except common human temptations, but God is faithful, who will not allow you* to be tempted beyond what you* are able to undergo, but with the temptation, he will also make* an outlet.'],
   ['Hence, my beloved, flee from idolatry.'],
   ['I speak as to prudent men. You* judge what I say.'],
   ['The cup of blessing for which we are giving-thanks, is it not a<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>fellowship of the blood of Christ? The bread which we are breaking, is it not a<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>fellowship of the body of Christ?'],
   ['Because we, who are many, are one bread, one body; for* we all are partaking from the one bread.'],
   ['Beware of Israel, according to the flesh: are not those who eat the sacrifices partners with the altar?'],
   ['Then what do I say? That an idol is anything or that an idol-sacrifice is anything?'],
   ['But I say, that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they are sacrificing to demons and not to God and I do not wish you* to become partners with demons.'],
   ['You* cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You* cannot partake of the table of the Lord and of the table of demons.'],
   ['Or are we provoking the Lord to jealousy? We are not mightier than him, are we?'],
   ['All things are legal for me, but not all things are advantageous. All things are legal for me, but not all things build up.'],
   ['Let no one seek his own, but each one seek the good of the other.'],
   ['Eat everything that is sold in the meat-markets, judging nothing because of conscience,'],
   ['for* the earth is the Lord&rsquo;s and its fullness.'],
   ['But if anyone of the unbelieving invites you* to a feast and you* wish to go; eat whatever is placed before you*, judging nothing because of conscience.'],
   ['But if anyone says to you*, This has been an idol-sacrifice, do not eat, because of him who divulged it and because of conscience; for* the earth is the Lord&rsquo;s and its fullness.'],
   ['I say, not your conscience, but conscience of the other; for* why is my freedom judged by another conscience?'],
   ['If I partake with gratitude, why am I blasphemed on behalf of what I give-thanks?'],
   ['Therefore whether you* eat or drink or whatever you* are doing, do all to the glory of God.'],
   ['Do not become a stumbling block, either to Jews or to Greeks or to the <font color=#808080>{F}</font> congregation* of God;'],
   ['just-as I am also pleasing all people in all things, not seeking what is advantageous for me, but what is advantageous for many, that* they may be saved.<font color=#FF0000></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Co 10:16- tradition and some translations used &lsquo;communion&rsquo; for the word &lsquo;fellowship&rsquo; which is the common translation throughout the rest of the New Covenant. 1Co 10:32 Or: church/the one true church, Eph 4:1-6; discussed more in the Appendix.}</font><font color=#FF0000></font> '],
  ],
  [ // 46:11
   ['Become imitators of me, just-as I also am of Christ.'],
   ['Now I praise you* brethren that you* have remembered me in all things and are holding-onto the traditions, just-as I gave them to you*.'],
   ['But I wish you* to know, that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of the woman is the man, and the head of Christ is God.'],
   ['Every man praying or prophesying, having something on his head, shames his head.'],
   ['But every woman praying or prophesying with her head unveiled shames her head; for* it is one and the same thing as if she were shaved.'],
   ['For* if a woman is not veiled, let her hair also be sheared, but if it is shameful to a woman to be sheared or shaved, let her be veiled.'],
   ['For* a man indeed ought not to have his head veiled, being* that he is the image and glory of God, but the woman is the glory of the man.'],
   ['For* the man is not from the woman, but the woman is from the man;'],
   ['for* neither was the man created because of the woman, but the woman because of the man.'],
   ['Because of this the woman ought to have a sign of authority upon her head, because of the messengers.'],
   ['However, neither is the man without the woman, nor the woman without the man, in the Lord.'],
   ['For* like the woman is from the man, so the man is also through the woman, but all things are from God.'],
   ['You* judge in yourselves. Is it suitable that a woman pray to God unveiled?'],
   ['Or does not even nature itself teach you*, that, if a man has long-hair, it is a dishonor to him?'],
   ['But if a woman has long-hair, it is a glory to her, because her hair is given to her instead of a head dressing.'],
   ['But if anyone seems to be contentious, we have no such custom, nor the congregations* of God.'],
   ['But in commanding this, I am not praising you*, because you* are not coming together *for the best but *for the worst.'],
   ['For* first of all, when you* come together in the congregation*, I am hearing that splits exist in you*, and I believe some part of it.'],
   ['For* there must also be sects among you*, that* those who are approved ones may become apparent among you*.'],
   ['Therefore when you* come together, it is not possible to eat the Lord&rsquo;s supper;'],
   ['for* in your* eating each one is taking his own supper before others can, and one is hungry and another is drunken.'],
   ['For* do you* not have houses in which to eat and drink in? Or do you* despise the <font color=#808080>{F}</font> congregation* of God and are shaming those who have nothing? What should I say to you*? Should I praise you*? I should not praise you* in this. <font color=#808080>{Mk 14:22-25 &amp; Mt 26:26-29 &amp; Lk 22:19-20, 1Cor: 11:23-26}</font>'],
   ['For* I received from the Lord what I also gave to you*, that the Lord Jesus in the night in which he was given up took bread;'],
   ['and when he had given-thanks, he broke it and said, <font color=#FF0000>Take, eat. This is my body, which is being broken on your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> behalf. Practice this in my remembrance.</font>'],
   ['Likewise* also the cup, after the supper, saying,<font color=#FF0000> This cup is the </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#FF0000> new covenant</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in my blood. Practice this in my remembrance whenever you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> drink </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['For* whenever you* eat this bread and drink this cup, you* are proclaiming the Lord&rsquo;s death until whenever he comes.'],
   ['So-then whoever unworthily eats this bread or drinks the cup of the Lord, will be liable to the body and of the blood of the Lord.'],
   ['But let a man test himself and so let him eat from the bread and drink out of the cup.'],
   ['For* he who unworthily eats and drinks, is eating and drinking judgment to himself, if he does not discern the body of the Lord.'],
   ['Because of this, many among you* are weak and sick and a considerable number fall-asleep.'],
   ['For* if we discerned ourselves, we should not be judged.'],
   ['But being judged, we are disciplined by the Lord, that* we may not be condemned with the world.'],
   ['So-then my brethren, when you* come together to eat, wait for one another.'],
   ['But if anyone is hungry, let him eat in his own house; that* you* may not come together *for judgment. And the rest I will set in order whenever I come.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Co 11:22 Or: church/the one true church, Eph 4:1-6; discussed more in the Appendix. 1Co 11:25 See Appendix under Covenant.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 46:12
   ['Now brethren, I do not wish you* to be ignorant concerning spiritual gifts.'],
   ['You* know that when you* were Gentiles you*<i> were</i> led away to those voiceless idols, as you* might be led now.'],
   ['Hence I make known to you*, that no one speaking in the Spirit of God says, Jesus is accursed, and no one can say, Jesus is Lord, except in the Holy Spirit.'],
   ['Now there are diversities of gifts*, but the same Spirit.'],
   ['And there are diversities of services and the same Lord.'],
   ['And there are diversities of workings, but it is the same God, who is working all things in all.'],
   ['But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for what is advantageous:'],
   ['for* the word of wisdom is given to one through the Spirit, and to another, the word of knowledge, according to the same Spirit;'],
   ['and to another, miraculous faith, in the same Spirit; and to another, gifts* of healing, in the same Spirit;'],
   ['and to another, workings of miracles; and to another, prophecy; and to another, the discerning of spirits; to another, varieties of languages; and to another, the translation of foreign languages;'],
   ['but the one and the same Spirit is working all these things, sectioning to each one in his own way just-as he wills.'],
   ['For* just-as the body is one and has many members and all the members of the one body, being many, are one body; so also is Christ.'],
   ['For* also, we were all immersed* into one body, in one Spirit, whether Jews or Greeks, whether bond or free, and all were given to drink into one Spirit.'],
   ['For* the body is not one member, but many.'],
   ['If the foot says, Because I am not the hand, I am not from the body; by this, is it not from the body?'],
   ['And if the ear says, Because I am not the eye, I am not from the body; by this, is it not from the body?'],
   ['If the whole body were an eye, where is the hearing? If the whole body were hearing, where is the sense of smell?'],
   ['But now God has placed the members, each one of them, in the body, just-as he willed.'],
   ['And if they were all one member, where is the body?'],
   ['But now they are indeed many members, but one body.'],
   ['And the eye cannot say to the hand, I have no need of you; or again the head to the feet, I have no need of you*.'],
   ['But much rather, those members of the body that seem to be* weak are necessary;'],
   ['and those parts of the body, which we think to be more dishonored, we place even-more honor upon these, and our indecent parts have even-more decency;'],
   ['but our decent parts have no need. But God mixed the body together, giving even-more honor to that part which lacks;'],
   ['that* no splits should be in the body, but that<i>*</i> the members should have the same anxiety on behalf of one another.'],
   ['And if one member is suffering, all the members are suffering with it. If one member is glorified, all the members are rejoicing with it.'],
   ['Now you* are the body of Christ and members individually.'],
   ['And God has placed some in the <font color=#808080>{F}</font> congregation*, first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, thereafter miracles, thereafter gifts* of healing, helps, those who pilot others, those with varieties of languages.'],
   ['All are not apostles, are they? All are not prophets, are they? All are not teachers, are they? All are not workers of miracles, are they?'],
   ['All do not have gifts* of healing, do they? All do not speak with foreign languages, do they? All do not translate, do they?'],
   ['But be zealous for the better gifts*. And I show to you* still a surpassingly-better way.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Co 12:28 Or: church/the one true church, Eph 4:1-6; discussed more in the Appendix.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 46:13
   ['If I speak with the languages of men and of messengers, but do not have love*, I have become like noisy brass or a clanging cymbal.'],
   ['And if I have the gift of prophecy and if I know all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith, so-then to remove mountains, but if I do not have love*, I am nothing.'],
   ['And if I handout all of my possessions and if I give my body that* I will be burned, but if I do not have love*, it profits me nothing.'],
   ['Love* is patient and is kind. Love* is not jealous. Love* does not brag, is not arrogant,'],
   ['does not behave improperly, does not seek its own, does not irritate, does not reason evil,'],
   ['does not rejoice in unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth.'],
   ['<i>Love</i>* forbears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.'],
   ['Love* never* falls short. But if there are prophesies, they will be done-away; if there are foreign languages, they will cease; if there is knowledge, it will be done-away.'],
   ['But we know in part and we prophesy in part;'],
   ['but whenever the finished thing comes, then what is in part will be done-away.'],
   ['When I was an infant, I spoke like an infant, I had the mind-set like that of an infant, I reasoned like an infant. Now that I have become a man, I have done-away-with the things of the infant.'],
   ['For* now we see in a mirror, dimly, but then face to face. I know now in part, but then I will fully know just-as I was also fully known.'],
   ['But these three are remaining now: faith, hope, love*, and the greatest of these is love*.  '],
  ],
  [ // 46:14
   ['Pursue love*; yet be zealous for spiritual gifts, but rather that* you* may prophesy.'],
   ['For* he who speaks in a foreign language does not speak to men, but to God; for* no one hears with understanding, but he speaks mysteries in the spirit.'],
   ['But he who prophesies speaks to men for building up and encouragement and consolation.'],
   ['He who speaks in a foreign language builds himself up, but he who prophesies builds up the congregation*.'],
   ['Now I wish for all of you* to speak with foreign languages, but more that* you* may prophesy, for* greater is he who is prophesying than he who is speaking with foreign languages, unless he translates, that* the congregation* may receive building up.'],
   ['But brethren, now if I come to you* speaking with foreign languages, what shall I profit you*, if I do not speak to you* either in revelation or in knowledge or in prophesying or in teaching?'],
   ['Even the lifeless things give forth a voice, whether flute or harp, if they do not give a distinction in the sounds, how shall it be known what is piped or harped?'],
   ['For* if the trumpet gives an indistinct voice, who will prepare himself *for war?'],
   ['So you* also, if you* do not give distinct speech through the foreign language, how shall it be known what is spoken? For* you* will be speaking into the air.'],
   ['If the foreign voices in the world are so-great, as it may be, and yet none are unintelligible.'],
   ['Therefore if I do not know the power of the voice, I will be a barbarian to him who speaks with it and he who speaks will be a barbarian to me.'],
   ['So you* also, since you* are zealous of spiritual gifts, seek in order that you* may abound to the building up of the congregation*.'],
   ['Hence let him who speaks in a foreign language pray in order that he may translate.'],
   ['For* if I pray in a foreign language, my spirit prays, but my mind is unfruitful.'],
   ['Then* what is it? I will pray with the spirit and I will also pray with the mind. I will sing-praise with the spirit and I will also sing-praise with the mind.'],
   ['Otherwise if you give-thanks with the spirit, how will he who fills the place of the unskilled say the amen upon your giving of thanks, since he does not know what you are saying?'],
   ['For* you indeed give-thanks well, but the other is not built up.'],
   ['I give-thanks to my God, I speak with foreign languages more than you* all.'],
   ['But in the congregation*, I wish to speak five words through my mind in order that I might also instruct others, than ten thousand words in a foreign language.'],
   ['Brethren, do not become children in your mind-sets, (but be infants in malice), but become mature in your mind-sets.'],
   ['It has been written in the law, &lsquo;I will speak to this people in other languages and by other lips, and thus they will not even hear me, says the Lord.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 28:11-12}</font>'],
   ['So-then foreign languages are *for a sign, not to those who believe, but to the unbelieving, but prophesying is for a sign, not to the unbelieving, but to those who believe.'],
   ['Therefore if the whole congregation* comes together and if all speak with foreign languages and if unskilled or unbelieving people come in, will they not say that you* are mad?'],
   ['But if all prophesy and some unbelieving or unskilled person comes in, he is<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>reproved by all. He is judged by all.'],
   ['And thus, the secrets of his heart become apparent, and so he will fall down upon his face and worship God, reporting that God really is among you*.'],
   ['Then* what is it, brethren? Whenever you* come together, each one of you* has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has a foreign language, has a translation. Let all things be done *for building up.'],
   ['If anyone speaks in a foreign language, let it be according to two or three at the most and up individually, and let one translate.'],
   ['But if there is no translator, let him be silent in the congregation*, and let him speak to himself and to God.'],
   ['And let the prophets speak by two or three and let the others discern.'],
   ['But if a prophesy is revealed to another sitting by, let the first be silent.'],
   ['For* you* all can prophesy one by one, that* all may learn and all may be encouraged.'],
   ['The spirits of the prophets are subject to the prophets;'],
   ['for* God is not a God of unrest, but of peace. As in all the congregations* of the holy-ones,'],
   ['let your* women be silent in the congregations*; for* it is not permitted for them to speak, but to be subject, as the law also says.'],
   ['And if they wish to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands in their own house; for* it is shameful for women to speak in a congregation*.'],
   ['What? Was it from you* that the word of God went forth? Or did it arrive only *for you*?'],
   ['If anyone thinks he is a prophet or spiritual, let him fully know of the things which I write to you*, that they are the commandments from the Lord.'],
   ['But if anyone is ignorant, let him be ignorant.'],
   ['So-then my brethren, be zealous to prophesy and do not forbid people to speak with foreign languages.'],
   ['But let all things be done decently and according to some order.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Co 14:24- Or: convicted.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 46:15
   ['Now I make known to you* brethren, the good-news which I proclaimed to you*, which you* also received, in which you* also stand,'],
   ['through which you* are also saved, if you* are holding-onto the word which I proclaimed to you*&ndash; unless you* vainly believed.'],
