   ['For* indeed he was sick&ndash; close to death. But God had mercy on him, now not him only, but also me, that* I might not have sorrow upon sorrow.'],
   ['Therefore I have sent him more diligently, that*, when you* see him again, you* may rejoice and that<i>*</i> I may be sorrow-free.'],
   ['Therefore accept him in the Lord with all joy, and hold such as admired;'],
   ['because he drew near almost as far as death, because of the work of the Christ, disregarding his life in order that* he might fill the lack in your* ministry* toward me.'],
