   ['I am pursuing the goal for the prize of the upward calling of God in Christ Jesus.'],
   ['Therefore as many as are mature, we should be mindful of this and if you* are mindful of anything differently, God will also reveal this to you*;'],
   ['however in what we have attained, let us march by the same standard*, let us be mindful of the same things.'],
   ['Brethren, become joint imitators with me, and note those who are walking so, just-as you* have us as an example .'],
   ['For* many are walking, (of whom I told you* often before and tell you* now even weeping), who are the enemies of the cross of Christ:'],
   ['whose end is destruction, whose god is the belly and whose glory is in their shame, who are mindful of earthly things.'],
   ['For* our citizenship exists in the heavens; out of which we are also waiting for a Savior, the Lord Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['He will fashion the body of our humbleness, *that* it may become transformed to the body of his glory according to the working of which he is able to even subject all things to himself.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Phil 3:6 Or: church/the one true church, Eph 4:1-6; discussed more in the Appendix.}</font>'],
  ],
  [ // 50:4
   ['So-then my brethren, beloved and longed for, my joy and crown, so stand fast in the Lord, my beloved.'],
   ['I am encouraging Euodia and I am encouraging Syntyche to be mindful of the same thing in the Lord.'],
   ['Yes, I am also requesting you, genuine colleague, help these women, who contended together with me in the good-news, with Clement also and the rest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the Book of Life.'],
   ['Rejoice in the Lord always. Again I will say, Rejoice.'],
   ['Let your* forbearance be known to all men. The Lord is near.'],
   ['Be anxious in nothing, but in everything let your* requests be made known to God by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving.'],
   ['And the peace of God, which is superior to every frame of mind, will guard your* hearts and your* minds in Christ Jesus.'],
   ['Furthermore brethren, as many things as are true, as many as are honorable, as many as are righteous, as many as are pure, as many as are lovely, as many as have good-repute; if there is any virtue and if there is any praise, reason on these things.'],
   ['The things which you* both learned and received and heard and saw in me, practice these things and the God of peace will be with you*.'],
   ['But I rejoice in the Lord greatly, that now at last, you* have bloomed again the desire to be mindful of things on my behalf; on this, you* were even mindful of me, but you* had no opportunity.'],
   ['Not that I am speaking according to my lack of things; for* I have learned to be content in whatever state I am in.'],
   ['I know how to be humbled and I also know how to abound. I have been initiated in everything and in all things, both to be well fed and to be hungry, both to abound and to fall-short.'],
   ['I am strong in all things in Christ who is empowering me.'],
   ['However you* did well, having shared with my affliction.'],
   ['Now you* also know, you* Philippians, that in the beginning of the good-news, when I went out from Macedonia, no congregation* shared with me in the<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>matter of the giving and receiving except you* only.'],
   ['Because even in Thessalonica you* sent once and then twice to my need.'],
   ['Not that I am seeking after a present, but I am seeking after the fruit that increases to your* account.'],
   ['But I have all things and I am abounding. I am filled, having accepted from Epaphroditus the things that came from you*, an aroma of a sweet-fragrance, an acceptable sacrifice, well pleasing to God.'],
   ['And my God will fill every need of yours* according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.'],
   ['Now to our God and Father be the glory forever and ever. Amen.'],
   ['Greet every holy-one in Christ Jesus. The brethren who are with me greet you*.'],
   ['All the holy-ones greet you*, especially those who are from Caesar&rsquo;s household.'],
   ['The grace of the Lord Jesus the Christ be with all of you*. Amen.<font color=#808080></font> {Footnotes: Phil 4:15- Greek: word. Or: The Word.}'],
