 [ // 52
  [
   ['Paul and Silvanus and Timothy to the congregation* of the Thessalonians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus the Christ: grace to you* and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['We are always giving-thanks to God concerning you* all, making* mention of you* in our prayers;'],
   ['constantly remembering your* work of the faith and labor of love* and endurance of hope in our Lord Jesus the Christ, in front of our God and Father,'],
   ['having known your* choice, brethren who are beloved by God.'],
   ['<i>You</i>*<i> know</i> because our good-news did not only come to you* in word, but also in power and in the Holy Spirit and in much full assurance; just-as you* know what manner of men we became among you* because of you*.'],
   ['And you* became imitators of us and of the Lord, having accepted the word in much affliction with joy of the Holy Spirit;'],
   ['so-that you* became examples to all who believe in Macedonia and in Achaia.'],
   ['For* the word of the Lord has echoed forth from you*, not only in Macedonia and in Achaia, but also in every place your* faith toward God has gone forth; so-that we do not need to say anything.'],
   ['For* they themselves are reporting concerning us what sort of entrance we had toward you* and how you* turned from idols to God and turned to serve* a living and true God,'],
   ['and to await his Son Jesus, from the heavens, whom he lifted up from the dead; who rescues us from the wrath to come. '],
  ],
  [ // 52:2
   ['For* brethren, you* yourselves know our entrance to you*, that it has not become empty.'],
   ['But having suffered before and been abused in Philippi, as you* know, we were bold in our God to speak to you* the good-news of God even with our great struggle.'],
   ['For* our encouragement is not from deceit, nor from uncleanness, nor in treachery.'],
   ['But just-as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the good-news, so we are speaking; not as pleasing men, but God who tests our hearts.'],
   ['For* as you* know, neither did we previously use words of flattery, nor by pretext of greed, (God is our witness);'],
   ['nor were we seeking glory from men, neither from you* nor from others, when we were able to burden you* as apostles of Christ.'],
   ['But we became mild in your* midst, as a nurse may cherish her own children.'],
   ['So having kindly-feelings of you*, we were delighted to have given to you*, not only the good-news of God, but also our own souls, because you* have become beloved to us.'],
   ['For* brethren, you* remember our labor and hardship. For* we were working night and day, *that* we might not burden any of you* while we preached to you* the good-news of God.'],
   ['You* and God are witnesses, how we became holy and righteous and blameless toward you* who believe.'],
   ['Just-as you* know how we dealt with each one of you*, like a father with his own children, encouraging you* and consoling you* and testifying,'],
   ['*that* you* should walk worthy of God, who calls you* into his own kingdom and glory.'],
   ['And because of this, we also are constantly giving-thanks to God, that, when you* accepted the word of God from our report, you* accepted it not as the word of men, but as it truly is, the word of God which is also working in you* who believe.'],
   ['For* brethren, you* became imitators of the {F} congregations* of God in Christ Jesus which are in Judea, because you* also suffered the same things by your* own countrymen, just-as they did by the Jews.'],
   ['<i>The Jews</i> who both killed the Lord Jesus and their own prophets and banished us and did not please God and are adverse to all men;'],
   ['forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles in order that they might be saved; *that* they should always fill up their sins, but the wrath has arrive-unexpectedly upon them&ndash; to the end.'],
   ['But brethren, being orphaned from you* in presence, but not in heart, even for a hour&rsquo;s time, we were even-more diligent to see your* face with great desire.'],
   ['Hence we wished to come to you*, indeed, I, Paul, once and again tried twice, and the Adversary hindered us.'],
   ['For* what is our hope or joy or crown of boasting, or is it not also you*, which is in front of our Lord Jesus the Christ at his presence?'],
   ['For* you* are our glory and our joy.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Th 2:14 Or: church/the one true church, Eph 4:1-6; discussed more in the Appendix.}</font>'],
