   ['and they may sober up out of the snare of the Devil, having been caught live by him to his will.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Please read the Preface. * is our universal footnoting for words contained in the Appendix. These words are NOT the same Greek word as the non-asterisk form; i.e. </font><font color=#FF0000>*for </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for* </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#808080>. 2Ti 2:4 OR: occupations of </font><i><font color=#808080>civilian</font></i><font color=#808080> life. 2Ti 2:15- Or: handling correctly. 1Ti 2:25- Or: disciplining OR correcting (an all inclusive word to describe what parents do for their children).}</font><font color=#808080></font> '],
