 [ // 57
  [
   ['Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus and Timothy our brother, to Philemon our beloved and fellow worker,'],
   ['and to Apphia the beloved and to Archippus our fellow soldier and to the congregation* in your house:'],
   ['grace to you* and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['I am always giving-thanks to my God, making* mention of you in my prayers,'],
   ['hearing of your love* and of the faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and toward all the holy-ones;'],
   ['*that the fellowship of your faith may become effective in the full knowledge of every good thing, which is in you*, to Christ Jesus.'],
   ['For* we have great gratitude and comfort in your love*, because the hearts* of the holy-ones have been given-rest through you, brother.'],
   ['Hence, having great boldness in Christ to command you what is proper,'],
   ['yet because of love* I would rather encourage you, being such a one as Paul the elderly-man and now also a prisoner of Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['I am encouraging you concerning my child, whom I have fathered in my bonds, Onesimus,'],
   ['who was not useful to you previously, but is useful to you now and to me whom I have sent back to you.'],
   ['But you receive him, that is, my heart*;'],
   ['whom I was intending to hold here with me, that* he might serve me in the bonds of the good-news on your behalf.'],
   ['But I wished to do nothing without your viewpoint; that* your good deed may not be as according to necessity, but willfully.'],
   ['For* perhaps because of this, he was separated from you for a season, in order that you may have him in the everlasting world;'],
   ['no longer as a bondservant, but beyond a bondservant, a beloved brother, especially to me, but how much rather to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.'],
   ['Therefore if you have me like a partner, receive him like myself.'],
   ['But if he has wronged you in anything or owes you anything, charge this to my account.'],
   ['I, Paul, write it with my own hand. I will compensate you; in order that I may not say to you, You are even owing yourself to me.'],
   ['Yes, brother, let me derive benefit from you in the Lord. Give-rest to my heart* in the Lord.'],
   ['I write to you, having confidence in your obedience, knowing that you will do even beyond what I am saying.'],
   ['But also at the same time, prepare me a lodging. For* I am hoping that through your* prayers I will be granted to you*.'],
   ['Epaphras, my fellow captive in Christ Jesus, greets you;'],
   ['<i>so do</i> my fellow workers Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, Luke.'],
   ['The grace of our Lord Jesus the Christ be with your* spirit. Amen.'],
  ],
