 [ // 59
  [
   ['James, a bondservant of God and of the Lord Jesus the Christ, to the twelve tribes those in the dispersion. Hail to you<i>*</i>!'],
   ['My brethren, deem it with all joy, whenever you* fall into various temptations,'],
   ['knowing that the testing of your* faith is working endurance.'],
   ['And let endurance have its perfect work, that* you* may be perfect and whole, lacking* in nothing.'],
   ['But if anyone of you* lacks* wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and does not reproach any, and it will be given to him.'],
   ['But let him ask in faith, doubting nothing. For* he who is doubting resembles a wave of the sea blown by the wind and tossed around.'],
   ['For* do not let that man assume that he will receive anything from the Lord&ndash;'],
   ['an indecisive man is restless in all his ways.'],
   ['Now let the humble brother boast in his elevation,'],
   ['but the rich brother in his humbleness, because like the flower of the grass, he will pass away.'],
   ['For* the sun has risen with the scorching heat and dried up the grass and its flower falls and the beauty of its face perished. So shall the rich man also fade away in his pursuits.'],
   ['The man who is enduring temptation is fortunate, because when he has been approved, he will receive the crown of life, which the Lord promised to those who love* him.'],
   ['Let no one say when he is tempted, I am tempted by God, for* God is not tempted by evils and he himself tempts no one.'],
   ['But each person is tempted, when he is drawn-away and enticed by his own lust.'],
   ['Thereafter when this lust has conceived, it bears sin and sin when it has matured, gives-birth to death.'],
   ['Do not be misled, my beloved brethren!'],
   ['Every good act of giving and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no change, nor a shadow of turning.'],
   ['Having willed it, he gave-birth to us by the word of truth, *that* we might be a kind of first-fruits of his created things.'],
   ['So-then my beloved brethren, let every man be quick in order to hear, slow in order to speak, and slow to wrath.'],
   ['For* the wrath of man is not working the righteousness of God.'],
   ['Hence having laid away from yourselves all filthiness and the abundance of malice, accept the implanted word with meekness, which is able to save your* souls.'],
   ['But be doers of the word and not hearers only, deluding yourselves.'],
   ['Because if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, he resembles a man considering his face (which was his from birth) in a mirror.'],
   ['For* he has considered himself and has gone away and immediately forgot what sort of man he was.'],
   ['But he who has peered into the perfect law, the law of freedom and remains in it, this one, having not become a forgetful hearer but a doer who works, this one will be fortunate<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>in his practices.'],
   ['If anyone among you* thinks himself to be religious, though he does not bridle his tongue but deceives his heart, this one&rsquo;s religion is futile.'],
   ['A clean and undefiled religion before our God and Father is this: to<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>visit<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>the orphans and widows in their affliction and to keep oneself unstained from the world.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: James 1:26- Or: actions, doings. James 1:27a- Many try to use the other meaning of this Greek word: oversee; James 1:27b Or: the fatherless. See the History Section in the Appendix. Please read the Preface. * is our universal footnoting for words contained in the Appendix. These words are NOT the same Greek word as the non-asterisk form; i.e. </font><font color=#FF0000>*for </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for* </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#808080>.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 59:2
   ['My brethren, do not have the faith of our Lord Jesus the Christ, the Lord of glory, with partiality.'],
   ['For* if a man comes into your* congregation* with a gold ring, in bright apparel and if a poor man in filthy apparel also comes in,'],
   ['you* may have looked upon him who is wearing the bright apparel and may have said to him, You sit here; good; and you* may have said to the poor person, You stand there or sit here under my footstool.'],
   ['And did you* not discern among yourselves and become judges with evil reasonings?'],
   ['Listen, my beloved brethren. Did God not choose the poor of the world to be rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom which he promised to those who love* him?'],
   ['But you* have dishonored the poor. Are the rich not oppressing you*? And are they not dragging you* into the courts?'],
   ['Are they not blaspheming the good name, the one which was named upon you*?'],
   ['Nevertheless, if you* accomplish the royal law, according to the Scripture, &lsquo;You will love* your neighbor like yourself,&rsquo; you* are doing well. <font color=#808080>{Lev. 19:18}</font>'],
   ['But if you* have shown-partiality, you* work sin, being convicted by the law as transgressors.'],
   ['For* whoever keeps the whole law and yet trips in one point, he has become liable to all of it.'],
   ['For* he who said, Do not commit adultery, also said, Do not murder. <font color=#808080>{Ex. 20:13-14, Deut. 5:17-18}</font> Now if you do not commit adultery, but murder, you have become a transgressor of the law.'],
   ['You* speak so and you* practice so, as men who are about to be judged by the law of freedom.'],
   ['For* judgment is merciless to him who has not practiced mercy; mercy wins over judgment.'],
   ['What does it profit, my brethren, if someone says he has faith, but does not have works? That faith cannot save him, can it?'],
   ['But if a brother or sister is* naked and may have a lack* of daily nourishment,'],
   ['and one out of you* may say to them, Go in peace. Be warmed and fed. And yet you* do not give them the body&rsquo;s requirements; what does it profit?'],
   ['So also your faith, if it does not have works, is dead in itself.'],
   ['But someone will say, You have faith, and I have works. Show me your faith away from your works. I will also show you my faith by my works.'],
   ['You believe that God is one; you are doing well. The demons also believe and shudder.'],
   ['But are you willing to know, O vain man, that faith is dead without works?'],
   ['Was not Abraham our father justified from works, when he offered up Isaac his son upon the altar?'],
   ['You see that faith was working together with his works and faith is perfected from works;'],
   ['and the Scripture was fulfilled which says, &lsquo;And Abraham believed God and it was counted to him *for righteousness&rsquo;, and he was called the friend of God. <font color=#808080>{Gen 15:6}</font>'],
   ['Now-then, you* see that a man is justified from works and not from faith alone.'],
   ['And likewise, was not Rahab the harlot also justified from works, in that she accepted the messengers and sent them out another way?'],
   ['For* as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is also dead. '],
