  [ // 59:3
   ['My brethren, do not let many of you* become teachers, knowing that we will receive greater judgment.'],
   ['For*we all trip in many things. If anyone does not trip in speech, this one is a perfect man, also able to bridle the whole body.'],
   ['Behold we put the horses&rsquo; bridles into their mouths that they may obey us, and we direct their whole body.'],
   ['Behold also the ships, though they are so-great and are driven by hard winds, yet they are directed by a small rudder, wherever the impulse of the steersman is intending.'],
   ['So the tongue is also a little member and boosts of magnificent things. Behold, how-vast a forest is lit by such a little fire!'],
   ['And the tongue is a fire, the world of unrighteousness. Thus the tongue is designated among our members as what stains the whole body and ignites the cycle of <font color=#808080>{F}</font> life and is ignited by hell.'],
   ['For* every nature of beasts and birds, of reptiles and sea-creatures, is tamed and has been tamed by human nature.'],
   ['But none of mankind is able to tame the tongue; it is an uncontrollable evil, it is full of deadly poison.'],
   ['We thank God and the Father with it and we curse men with it, those who became according to the likeness of God.'],
   ['Thanks and cursing comes out from the same mouth. My brethren, these things do not need to become so!'],
   ['The spring is not gushing sweet and bitter water from the same hole in the ground, is it?'],
   ['My brethren, a fig tree is not able to produce olives or a vine figs, are they? Thus no spring is able to produce both salty and sweet water.'],
   ['Who is wise and knowledgeable among you*? Let him show out of his good conduct his works in meekness of wisdom.'],
   ['But if you* have bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your* heart, do not boast and lie against the truth.'],
   ['This wisdom is not a wisdom that comes down from above, but is earthly, physical, demonic.'],
   ['For* where jealousy and selfish ambition are, there is unrest and every evil matter.'],
   ['But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, thereafter is peaceful, gentle, compliant, full of mercy and good fruits,<font color=#808080> </font>impartial and without hypocrisy.'],
   ['And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those who are making* peace.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: James 3:6- Literally: birth or origin or generations. }</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 59:4
   ['From where do the wars and quarrels among you* come from? Is it not from here, from your* own sensual-delights which are warring in your* members?'],
   ['You* lust and do not have; you* murder and are jealous and cannot obtain; you* quarrel and make war; you* do not have, because you* do not ask.'],
   ['You* ask and do not receive, because you* ask evilly, that* you* may spend it in your* sensual-delights.'],
   ['Adulterers and adulteresses, do you* not know that the friendship of the world is enmity with God? Therefore whoever wills to be a friend of the world is standing as an enemy of God.'],
   ['Or are you* thinking that the Scripture speaks with emptiness? Does the Spirit which dwells in us long to envy?'],
   ['But he is giving more grace. Hence the Scripture says, &lsquo;God resists the haughty, but gives grace to the humble.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Prov 3:34}</font>'],
   ['Therefore be subject to God and withstand the Devil and he will flee from you*.'],
   ['Draw near to God and he will draw near to you*. You* sinners! You* indecisive! Cleanse your* hands and purify your* hearts!'],
   ['Be miserable and mourn and weep. Let your* laughter be turned to mourning and your* joy to gloom.'],
   ['Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord and he will exalt you*.'],
   ['Brethren do not speak against one another. He who is speaking against a brother and is judging his brother, is speaking against the law and is judging the law. Now if you are judging the law, you are not a doer of the law, but a judge.'],
   ['There is the one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy; who are you who judges another?'],
   ['Come now, you* who are saying, Today and tomorrow, we should go into this city and spend one year there and be a merchant and make* a gain.'],
   ['You* do not know what tomorrow will bring, for* what is your* life? For* it is a vapor, which appears for a little while and thereafter disappears.'],
   ['Instead of that, you* should say, If the Lord wills, and we should also live, then we may do this or that.'],
   ['But now you* boast in your* egotism. All such boasting is evil.'],
   ['Therefore knowing to do good and not doing it, to him, it is sin. '],
  ],
  [ // 59:5
   ['Come now you<i>*</i> rich, weep, howling in your* miseries, which are coming upon you*.'],
   ['Your* riches have rotted and your* garments have become moth-eaten.'],
   ['Your* gold and silver have tarnished, and their tarnish will be *for a testimony against you* and will eat your* flesh like fire. You* have stored up treasure in the last days.'],
   ['Behold, the wages of the workers who mowed your* farmlands, these wages which have been defrauded by you*, are crying out against you* and the cries of those who reaped have entered into the ears of the Lord of Hosts.'],
   ['You* have caroused upon the land and are self-indulgent; you* have nourished your* hearts as in a day of slaughter.'],
   ['You* have sentenced others, you* have murdered the righteous; he is not resisting you*.'],
   ['Therefore brethren, be patient until the presence of the Lord. Behold, the farmer who is waiting for the precious fruit of the earth, is patient over it, until it might receive the morning and evening rainfall.'],
   ['You* also be patient; establish your* hearts, because the presence of the Lord has drawn near.'],
   ['Brethren, do not groan against one another, that* you* may not be judged. Behold, the judge stands before the doors.'],
   ['Brethren, take as an example of suffering evil treatment and of patience the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord.'],
   ['Behold, we esteem those fortunate who are enduring. You* have heard of the endurance of Job and have seen the end of the Lord, how that he is very affectionate and compassionate.'],
   ['But before all things my brethren, do not swear, neither by the heaven, nor by the earth, nor by any other oath, but let your* yes be yes and your* no be no; that* you* may not fall into hypocrisy.'],
   ['Is anyone among you* suffering evil treatment? Let him pray. Is anyone cheerful? Let him sing-praise.'],
   ['Is anyone among you* sick? Let him call for the elders of the congregation*, and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord.'],
   ['And the prayer of the faith will save him who is weary and the Lord will lift him up, even if he has been practicing sins, it will be forgiven him.'],
   ['Therefore confess your* trespasses to one another and pray on behalf of one another, *that you* may be healed. The supplication of a righteous man prevails&ndash; great in its working.'],
   ['Elijah was a man of like-feelings with us and he prayed with intense prayer that it might not rain, and it did not rain upon the land for three years and six months.'],
   ['And he prayed again, and the heaven gave rainfall and the land sprouted her fruit.'],
   ['Brethren, if anyone among you* are misled from the truth and someone should return him to it;'],
