 [ // 60
  [
   ['Peter, an apostle of Jesus the Christ, to the chosen who are travelers of the dispersion in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia and Bithyna,'],
   ['according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, in the sanctification of the Spirit, to obedience and sprinkling of the blood of Jesus the Christ: grace to you* and may peace be multiplied.'],
   ['The God and Father of our Lord Jesus the Christ is gracious*, who according to his great mercy has born us again to a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus the Christ from the dead,'],
   ['to an incorruptible inheritance, undefiled and unfading, guarded in the heavens *for you*.'],
   ['<i>You</i>* who by the power of God are being kept through faith to a salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.'],
   ['In which you* are glad, though now for a little while, if it is essential, having been sorrowful in various tests,'],
   ['that* the trial of your* faith, (being more precious than gold, which is perishing), even now being proven through fire, may be found *for praise and honor and to glory in the revelation of Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['Whom, though having not seen him, you* love*; in whom, though now you* do not see him, yet believing, you* are glad with joy unspeakable and glorified;'],
   ['getting to the end of your* faith, that is the salvation of your* souls.'],
   ['Concerning which salvation the prophets, who prophesied concerning the grace that should come to you*, sought out and searched out;'],
   ['searching what time or what sort of time the Spirit of Christ in them indicated, when it testified beforehand the sufferings of Christ and the glories following after these things.'],
   ['To whom it was revealed, that they were not serving themselves, but to you* the same things, which now have been reported to you* through those who proclaimed the good-news to you* in the Holy Spirit sent forth from heaven; which things messengers desire to peer into.'],
   ['Hence girding up the loins of your* mind, be sober and hope perfectly upon the grace being brought to you* in the revelation of Jesus the Christ;'],
   ['like children of obedience not fashioning yourselves to your* former lusts in the time of your* ignorance;'],
   ['but just-as he who called you* is holy, you* yourselves also become holy in all your* conduct;'],
   ['because it has been written, &lsquo;Become holy, because I am holy.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Lev. 11:44-45, 19:2, 20:7,26}</font>'],
   ['And if you* call on the Father, who judges without showing partiality according to each one&rsquo;s work, conduct yourselves in fear during the time of your* foreign residency here;'],
   ['knowing that you* were not redeemed with corruptible things&ndash; with silver or with gold, nor from your* futile conduct handed down from your* forefathers.'],
   ['But as of a lamb unblemished and unstained, you were redeemed with precious blood of Christ:'],
   ['who indeed, having been known beforehand, before the conception of the world, but was manifested upon the last times because of you*,'],
   ['who, through him, believe in God who lifted him up from the dead and gave him glory; so-that your* faith and hope might be in God.'],
   ['Seeing you* have purified your* souls in your* obedience to the truth through the Spirit toward brotherly-love without hypocrisy, intensely love* one another from a clean heart;'],
   ['having been born again, not out of corruptible seed, but from the incorruptible, through the word of God, which is living and remaining forever.'],
   ['Because, &lsquo;All flesh is like grass and all the glory of man is like the flower of grass. The grass dried up and the flower of it fell away.'],
   ['But the word of the Lord is abiding forever.&rsquo;<font color=#808080> {Is. 40:6-9}</font> And this is the word of the good-news which was proclaimed to you*. '],
  ],
  [ // 60:2
   ['Therefore having placed away from yourselves all malice and all treachery and hypocrisies and envies and all slanders,'],
   ['as newborn babies, long for the logical milk which is without treachery, that* you* may grow in it;'],
   ['if indeed, you* have tasted that the Lord is kind;'],
   ['coming to him, a living stone, indeed rejected* by men, but with God chosen and precious.'],
   ['You*, like living stones, are also built up as a spiritual house, to be a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God through Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['Because it is contained in Scripture, &lsquo;Behold, I place in Zion a cornerstone, chosen and precious and he who believes in him may never* be ashamed.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 28:16}</font>'],
   ['Therefore to you* who believe is the honor, but to the disobedient, &lsquo;The stone which the builders rejected*, this became the head of the corner;&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Ps. 118:22}</font>'],
   ['and, &lsquo;A stone of stumbling and a rock of offense;&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Is. 8:14}</font> to those who are stumbling in the word, being disobedient; also they were appointed* *for that.'],
   ['But you* are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people *for God&rsquo;s ownership, *that you* may proclaim the virtues of him who called you* out of darkness into his marvelous light;'],
   ['who previously were no people, but now are the people of God; who had not been shown-mercy, but now have been shown-mercy.'],
   ['Beloved, I am encouraging you* to be like foreigners and travelers, to abstain from fleshly lusts, which are warring against the soul;'],
   ['having your* good conduct seen among the Gentiles; that*, in what they are speaking against you*, like evildoers, they may (having been eyewitnesses from your* good works) glorify God in the day of visitation.'],
   ['Therefore be subject to every human creation because of the Lord: whether to the king, as he is superior to you*;'],
   ['or to governors, as they are sent through him *for vengeance on evildoers and praise to those who do good.'],
   ['Because so is the will of God, that by doing good you* might hush the ignorance of foolish men;'],
   ['as free and yet not having your* freedom as a covering of malice, but as bondservants of God.'],
   ['Honor all men. Love* the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the king.'],
