  [ // 60:5
   ['I am encouraging the elders who are among you*, as I, who am a fellow elder and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and a partner of the glory which is about to be revealed,'],
   ['<i>to</i> shepherd the flock of God which is among you*, exercising the oversight, not by compulsion, but willfully, and not covetously, but eagerly;'],
   ['and not like one lording it over his lot, but you* yourselves become examples to the flock.'],
   ['And when the Chief-Shepherd is manifested, you* will get the unfading crown of glory.'],
   ['Likewise, you* the younger, be subject to the elder. And all of you* be subject to one another, clothe yourself with humility, because &lsquo;God resists the haughty, but is giving grace to the humble.&rsquo; <font color=#808080>{Prov. 3:34}</font>'],
   ['Therefore humble yourselves under the powerful hand of God, that* he may exalt you* in time;'],
   ['tossing all your* anxiety upon him, because with him there is care concerning you*.'],
   ['Be sober! Be watchful! Your* opponent, the Devil, like a roaring lion, is walking around seeking whom he may swallow,'],
   ['to whom you* withstand, solid in the faith, knowing that the same sufferings are accomplished in your* brotherhood which is in the world.'],
   ['And the God of all grace, who called you* to his everlasting glory in Christ Jesus, after you* have suffered a little while, he himself may perfect you*, may establish, may strengthen and may found you<i>*</i>.'],
   ['To him is the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.'],
   ['Through Silvanus, our faithful brother, as I count him, I have written to you* through a very few words, encouraging and testifying that this is the true grace of God into which you* have stood fast.'],
   ['She who is in Babylon, chosen together with you*, greets you*, and so does Mark my son.'],
   ['Greet one another with a kiss of love*. Peace be to you* all who are in Christ Jesus. Amen.'],
