   ['If anyone sees his brother sinning <font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>sin not to death, he will ask and God will give him life for those who are not sinning to death. There is <font color=#808080>{F}</font> sin to death. I do not say that* he should ask concerning that.'],
   ['All unrighteousness is sin and there is sin not leading to death.'],
   ['We know that everyone who has been born from God is not sinning, but he who was born from God guards himself and the evil one does not touch him.'],
   ['We know that we are from God and the whole world lies in the evil one.'],
   ['And we know that the Son of God has come and has given us perception, that* we might know him who is true and we are in him who is true, that is in his son, Jesus the Christ. He is the true God and everlasting life.'],
   ['<i>My</i> little children, guard yourselves from idols. Amen.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 1Jn 5.7b-8a is not in most of the Greek Manuscripts. It was put there from the Catholic </font>Latin Bible. 1Jn 5:16a- Or: a sin not <i><font color=#808080>leading</font></i><font color=#808080> to death. 1Jn 5:16b- Or: a sin </font><i><font color=#808080>leading</font></i><font color=#808080> to death.}</font>'],
  ],
 ],
 [ // 63
  [
   ['The elder to the chosen<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>lady and her children, whom I love* in truth, and not only I, but also all those who know the truth;'],
   ['because of the truth which abides in us and it will be with us forever.'],
   ['Grace, mercy, peace will be with us, from God the Father and from the Lord Jesus the Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love*.'],
   ['I rejoice exceedingly that I have found some out of your children walking in truth, just-as we received commandment to us from the Father.'],
   ['And now I ask you<font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font>lady, not as though I write to you a new commandment, but what we had from the beginning, that* we should love* one another.'],
   ['And this is love*, that* we should walk after his commandments. This is the commandment, just-as you* heard from the beginning, that* you* should walk in it.'],
   ['Because many misleaders have entered into the world, those who are not confessing Jesus the Christ as coming in the flesh. This is the misleader and the antichrist.'],
   ['You* beware in yourselves, that* you* should not destroy the things which we have worked in you*, but that<i>*</i> we may receive a full reward.'],
   ['Everyone who transgresses and does not abide in the teaching of Christ, does not have God. He who abides in the teaching of Christ, this one has both the Father and the Son.'],
   ['If anyone is coming to you* and is not bringing this teaching, do not receive him into your* house and do not say hello to him;'],
   ['for* he who says hello to him is sharing in his evil works.'],
   ['Having many things to write to you*, I did not intend to write them with paper and ink, but I am hoping to come to you* and to speak <font color=#808080>{F}</font> mouth to mouth, that* our joy may be fulfilled.'],
   ['The children of your chosen sister greet you. Amen.<font color=#808080></font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 2Jn 1:1,5- Or: Kyria; (A proper name). Lady is most likely a salutation like &lsquo;Sir&rsquo; or &lsquo;Lady,&rsquo; used figuratively for a congregation* which fits the plural you* &amp; singular you in verse 12-13) 2Jn 1:12- i.e., face to face.}</font>'],
  ],
 ],
 [ // 64
  [
   ['The elder to Gaius the beloved, whom I love* in truth.'],
   ['Beloved, I am praying for you to prosper and to be healthy concerning all things, just-as your soul prospers.'],
   ['For* I rejoiced exceedingly of brethren coming and testifying of your truth, just-as you are walking in truth.'],
   ['I have no greater joy than these things, that* I may hear my children are walking in the truth.'],
   ['Beloved, you practice faithfully whatever work you do toward the brethren and toward strangers;'],
   ['who testified to your* love* before the congregation*; whom you will do well to send onward worthily of God.'],
   ['For* on behalf of the Name they went forth, taking nothing from the Gentiles.'],
   ['Therefore we ought to receive such people, that* we may become fellow workers with the truth.'],
   ['I wrote to the congregation*, but Diotrephes, who loves to be foremost among them, is not accepting us.'],
   ['Because of this, if I come, I will bring to remembrance his works which he practices, gossiping against us with evil words and not content with these, he himself does not accept the brethren and those who intend to come, he forbids and casts them out of the congregation*.'],
   ['Beloved, do not imitate what is evil, but what is good. He who practices good is from God. He who practices evil has not seen God.'],
   ['Demetrius was testified of by all and by the truth itself. But we also are testifying and you* know that our testimony is true.'],
   ['I had many things to write to you, but I do not wish to write them to you with ink and reed.'],
   ['But I hope to see you immediately and we will speak <font color=#808080>{F}</font> mouth to mouth. Peace to you*. The friends greet you*. Greet the friends according to name.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: 3Jn 1:14, i.e., face to face.}</font>'],
  ],
 ],
 [ // 65
  [
   ['Jude, a bondservant of Jesus the Christ and brother of James, to the called who are sanctified in God the Father and kept in Jesus the Christ:'],
   ['mercy to you*, and may peace and love* be multiplied.'],
   ['Beloved, while I was making* all diligence to write to you* concerning our common salvation, I had a necessity to write to you* encouraging you* to earnestly fight for the faith given once for all to the holy-ones.'],
   ['For* some men sneaked in among you<i>*</i>, those who have been written about, from long-ago *for this condemnation of the ungodly, who are transferring the grace of our God into unbridled-lusts and denying our only Master, God the Father, and our Lord Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['And I intend to remind you*, though you* have fully known this once, that the Lord, when he had saved people out of the land of Egypt; that secondly he destroyed those who did not believe.'],
   ['And the messengers who did not keep to their own principality, but left their own house, he keeps to the judgment of the great day in eternal bonds under blackness.'],
   ['As Sodom and Gomorrah and the cities around them in a similar manner with these, having indulged in fornication and having gone after other flesh, lay before us as an example, held under the sentence of everlasting fire. <font color=#808080>{Gen 19:1-38}</font>'],
   ['Nevertheless, these dreaming likewise also are defiling the flesh and are rejecting lordship and are blaspheming the heavenly glories.'],
   ['But Michael the archangel, when arguing with the Devil, after he reasoned concerning the body of Moses, he did not dare to bring a judging of blasphemy against him, but said, The Lord rebuke you. <font color=#808080>{Deut 34: 5,6}</font>'],
   ['But these men, they blaspheme as many things as they do not know. And as many things as they know naturally, like the unreasoning creatures they are, they corrupt themselves in those things.'],
   ['Woe to them! Because they went in the way of Cain and poured themselves into the error of Balaam&rsquo;s reward and perished in the dispute of Korah. <font color=#808080>{Gen 4:8; Num 22:1-41; Num 16:1-50}</font>'],
   ['These people are hidden-reefs in your* love-feasts, sumptuously feasting alongside you* without fear, shepherding themselves, they are waterless clouds, carried around by the winds; unfruitful autumn trees, twice dead, uprooted,'],
   ['wild waves of the sea, foaming forth their own shames, misleading stars&ndash; for whom the blackness of darkness has been kept forever.'],
   ['And Enoch, seventh from Adam, also prophesied about these people, saying, Behold, the Lord <font color=#808080>{F} </font>came in among tens of thousands of his holy-ones,'],
   ['to make a judgment against all, and to convict all the ungodly of them, concerning all their works of ungodliness which they did in ungodly ways and concerning all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.'],
   ['These men are murmurers, complainers, conducting-themselves according to their lusts and their mouth is speaking flattering-words, admiring faces because of profit.'],
   ['But you*, beloved, remember the words which have been spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Jesus the Christ;'],
   ['that they told you* that in the last time there will be mockers, conducting-themselves according to their own lusts of ungodliness.'],
   ['These are the ones who are causing-splits, who are physical, not having the Spirit.'],
   ['But as for you*, beloved, keep building yourselves up in your* most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit.'],
   ['Keep yourselves in God&rsquo;s love*, waiting for the mercy of our Lord Jesus the Christ *for everlasting life.'],
   ['And show-mercy on some, making a distinction;'],
   ['but save others with fear, seizing them out of the fire, hating even the tunic stained from the flesh.'],
   ['Now to him who is able to guard us from falling and to stand us in the sight of his glory unblemished in gladness,'],
   ['to the only wise God our Savior, is the glory and majesty, dominion and authority, both now and forever. Amen.<font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Jude 1:14- Or: with tens of thousands </font><i><font color=#808080>of</font></i><font color=#808080> his holy-ones, Or: with his holy tens of thousands. * is our universal footnoting for words contained in the Appendix. These words are NOT the same Greek word as the non-asterisk form; i.e. </font><font color=#FF0000>*for </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for* </font><font color=#808080>is different from </font><font color=#FF0000>for</font><font color=#808080>.}</font>'],
  ],
 ],
 [ // 66
  [
   ['The Revelation of Jesus the Christ, which God gave him to show to his bondservants; the things that must happen shortly and he sent and signified it through his messenger to his bondservant John;'],
   ['who testifies of the word of God and of the testimony of Jesus the Christ; as many things as he saw.'],
   ['He who reads and those who hear the words of the prophecy and are keeping the things which have been written in it are fortunate; for* the time is near.'],
   ['John to the seven congregations* which are in Asia: grace to you* and peace from God who is and who was and who is to come, and from the seven spirits that are before his throne;'],
   ['and from Jesus the Christ, who is the faithful witness, the firstborn from the dead and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves* us and bathed us from our sins in his blood;'],
   ['and he made* us a kingdom, priests to his God and Father; to him is the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.'],
   ['Behold, he is coming with the clouds, and every eye will see him and those who stabbed him, and all the tribes of the earth will grieve over him. Yes he comes, Amen.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I am the Alpha and the Omega, says the Lord God, Who is and who was and who is to come, the Almighty</font>.'],
   ['I John, your* brother and partner with you* in affliction and the kingdom and endurance which are in Christ Jesus, was on the island called Patmos, because of the word of God and because of the testimony of Jesus the Christ.'],
   ['I became in the spirit on the Lord&rsquo;s day and I heard behind me a great voice, like that of a trumpet'],
   ['saying, <font color=#FF0000>What you see, write in a book and send </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> to the seven congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>: to Ephesus and to Smyrna and to Pergamus and to Thyatira and to Sardis and to Philadelphia and to Laodicea.</font>'],
   ['And I turned there to see the voice which spoke with me. And having turned I saw seven golden lamp-stands;'],
   ['and in the middle of the seven lamp-stands one similar to a son of man, clothed with a long-robe and girded around the breasts with a golden belt.'],
   ['And his head and his hair were white like white wool, like snow, and his eyes were like a flame of fire;'],
   ['and his feet similar to polished brass, as if they had been refined in a furnace, and his voice like the voice of many waters.'],
   ['And he had in his right hand seven stars and a sharp two edged sword came out from his mouth and his appearance was as the sun appears in its power.'],
   ['And when I saw him, I fell before his feet like one dead. And he placed his right hand upon me, saying, <font color=#FF0000>Do not fear; I am the first and the last,</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and the Living One, and I was dead and behold, I am living forever and ever and I have the keys of death and of Hades. Amen.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore write the things which you saw and the things which are and the things which are about to happen after these things.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>The mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right </font><i><font color=#FF0000>hand</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and the seven golden lamp-stands </font><i><font color=#FF0000>is this</font></i><font color=#FF0000>: the seven stars are the messengers of the seven congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> and the seven lamp-stands are seven congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 66:2
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Ephesus:</font> He who is holding-fast the seven stars in his right <i><font color=#FF0000>hand</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and who is walking in the middle of the seven golden lamp-stands says these things:</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works and your labor and endurance and that you are not able to bear evil men and you </font>tested those who are calling themselves to be apostles and are not and found them false;'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and you have endurance and did bear because of my name and have not fatigued.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But I have </font><i><font color=#FF0000>this</font></i><font color=#FF0000> against you; that you left your first love</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore remember from where you have fallen and repent and do the first works; otherwise I am coming to you shortly and will move your lamp-stand out of its place, if you do not repent.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But this you have, that you hate the works of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>. To him who is overcoming, I will give to him to eat from the Tree of Life, which is in </font><i><font color=#FF0000>the</font></i><font color=#FF0000> middle of the Paradise of God.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Smyrna:</font> The first and the last, who was dead and lived <i><font color=#FF0000>again</font></i><font color=#FF0000> says these things:</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works, your affliction and your poverty (but you are rich) and the blasphemy of those who say they are Jews and they are not, but are a synagogue of the Adversary.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>No one fear the things which you are about to suffer. Behold indeed, the Devil is about to cast </font><i><font color=#FF0000>some</font></i><font color=#FF0000> from you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> into prison, in order that you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> may be tested and you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will have affliction ten days. You be faithful to death and I will give you the crown of life.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>. He who is overcoming may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> be hurt from the second death.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Pergamus:</font> He who has the sharp two edged sword says these things:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works and where you dwell&ndash; where the Adversary&rsquo;s throne is, and you are holding-fast my name and did not deny my faith in the days of Antipas, my witness, my faithful one, who was killed before you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>, where the Adversary is dwelling.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But I have a few things against you, because you have there </font><i><font color=#FF0000>some</font></i><font color=#FF0000> holding-fast the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to cast an offense before the sons of Israel, to eat idol-sacrifices and to fornicate.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>So you also have </font><i><font color=#FF0000>some </font></i><font color=#FF0000>holding-fast the similar teaching of the Nicolaitans.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore repent; otherwise I am coming to you shortly and make war with them with the sword of my mouth.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>. To him who is overcoming, I will give to him to eat from the hidden manna and I will give him a white voting-pebble and a new name written upon the voting-pebble, which no one knows except he who is receiving it.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Thyatira:</font> The Son of God, who has his eyes like a flame of fire and his feet are similar to polished brass says these things:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works and love</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> and faith and service and endurance and that your last works are more-than the first.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But I have </font><i><font color=#FF0000>this</font></i><font color=#FF0000> against you, that you are allowing</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#808080>{F}</font><font color=#808080> </font><font color=#FF0000>your woman Jezebel, she who calls herself a prophetess, and she </font><i><font color=#FF0000>who</font></i><font color=#FF0000> is teaching and misleading my bondservants to fornicate and to eat idol-sacrifices.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And I gave her time, in order that she might repent, and she is not willing to repent from her fornication.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Behold, I cast her onto a bed and those who are committing adultery with her into great affliction, if they do not repent from her works.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And I will kill her children with death, and all the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> will know that I am he who is searching the brains and hearts and I will give to each one of you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> according to your</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> works.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But I say to you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> and to the rest who are in Thyatira, as many as are not holding </font><i><font color=#FF0000>to</font></i><font color=#FF0000> this teaching, who did not know the deep </font><i><font color=#FF0000>things</font></i><font color=#FF0000> of the Adversary, as they are saying. I cast upon you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> no </font>other burden.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>However hold-fast </font><i><font color=#FF0000>to</font></i><font color=#FF0000> what you</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> have, until whenever I have come.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he who is overcoming and he who is keeping my works to the end, to him I will give authority over the nations.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And he will shepherd them with an iron rod, as the vessels of the potter are crushed; as I have also received of my Father;</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>and I will give him the morning star.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font><font color=#808080> {Footnotes: Re 2:20- Or maybe: your wife Jezebel.}</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 66:3
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Sardis:</font> He who has the seven spirits of God and the seven stars says these things: I know your works, that you have a name, that you live; and you are dead.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Become watchful and establish the rest of the things, which are about to be cast away; for</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> I have not found your works fulfilled before my God.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Therefore remember how you have received and heard, and you keep </font><i><font color=#FF0000>it</font></i><font color=#FF0000> and repent. Therefore if you do not watch, I will come upon you like a thief and you may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> know what hour I will come upon you.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>But you have a few names in Sardis who did not defile their garments and they will walk with me in white, because they are worthy.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who is overcoming this, he will be dressed in white garments, and I will never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> wipe-away his name out of the Book of Life and I will confess his name before my Father and before his messengers.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Philadelphia:</font> He who is holy, who is true, who has the key of David, who opens and no one will lock and who locks and no one opens.'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works (behold, I have given </font><i><font color=#FF0000>you</font></i><font color=#FF0000> an opened door </font><i><font color=#FF0000>which is</font></i><font color=#FF0000> before you, which no one can lock), that you have little power and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>you have</font></i><font color=#FF0000> kept my word and did not deny my name.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Behold, I give </font><i><font color=#FF0000>them</font></i><font color=#FF0000> from the synagogue of the Adversary, those who say they are Jews and they are not, but are lying. Behold, I will make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> them that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> they should come and should worship before your feet and should know that I have loved</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because you kept the word of my endurance, I also will keep you from the hour of testing, that </font><i><font color=#FF0000>hour</font></i><font color=#FF0000> which is about to come upon the whole inhabited-earth, to test those who are dwelling upon the earth.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I am coming shortly. Hold-fast what you have, in order that no one may take your crown.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who is overcoming, I will make</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> him a pillar in the temple of my God and he may never</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> go outside any more and I will write upon him the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem, which comes down out of heaven from my God and my own new name.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>And write to the messenger of the congregation</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> in Laodicea:</font> The Amen, the faithful and true witness, the beginning of the creation of God, says these things:'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot. I wish-that you might be cold or hot.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>So because you are lukewarm and not hot nor cold, I am about to puke you out of my mouth.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Because you say, I am rich and have been enriched and have need of nothing, and do not know that you are the miserable and the pitiful and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>are</font></i><font color=#FF0000> poor and blind and naked.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>I am counseling you to buy gold from me, refined from fire, in order that you may be enriched, and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>with</font></i><font color=#FF0000> white </font>garments, that<font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you may dress yourself and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>that</font></i><i><font color=#FF0000>*</font></i><font color=#FF0000> the shame of your nakedness may not be made manifest, and that</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000> you may anoint your eyes with eye-salve, in order that you may see.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>As many as I may love, I reprove and discipline; therefore be zealous and repent.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>Behold, I stand at the door and knock; if anyone hears my voice and </font><i><font color=#FF0000>if</font></i><font color=#FF0000> he opens the door, I will go in to him and will dine with him and he with me.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who is overcoming, I will give to him to sit with me in my throne, as I also overcame and sat down with my Father in his throne.</font>'],
   ['<font color=#FF0000>He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the congregations</font><font color=#FF0000>*</font><font color=#FF0000>.</font> '],
  ],
  [ // 66:4
   ['After these things I saw and behold, a door had opened in heaven and the first voice which I heard, a voice like that of a trumpet speaking with me, saying, Come up here and I will show you the things which must happen after these things.'],
   ['And immediately I became in the spirit and behold, a throne was laying in heaven and he was sitting upon the throne,'],
   ['and he who was sitting, was similar in appearance to a jasper stone and a carnelian and there was a rainbow surrounding the throne, similar in appearance to an emerald.'],
   ['And twenty-four thrones were surrounding the throne and twenty-four elders sitting upon the thrones, dressed in white garments, and upon their heads golden crowns.'],
   ['And lightning and voices and thunders come out from the throne. And there were seven torches of fire burning before the throne, which are the seven spirits of God;'],
   ['and before his throne, like a glassy sea similar to crystal, and in the middle of the throne and surrounding the throne, four living creatures full of eyes in front of and behind.'],
   ['And the first living creature was similar to a lion and the second living creature was similar to a calf and the third living creature having a face like that of a man and the fourth living creature was similar to a flying eagle.'],
   ['And the four living creatures, every one of them having six wings apiece, are full of eyes, surrounding and inside and they have no rest day and night, saying, Holy, holy, holy, is the Lord God, the Almighty, who was and who is and who is to come.'],
   ['And whenever the living creatures gave glory and honor and thanks to him who is sitting upon the throne, to him who lives forever and ever,'],
   ['the twenty-four elders will fall down before him who is sitting upon the throne and will worship him who is living forever and ever and will cast their crowns before the throne, saying,'],
   ['Worthy are you, our Lord and our God&ndash; the holy one, to receive the glory and the honor and the power because you created all things and because they are your will and were created. '],
  ],
  [ // 66:5
   ['And I saw upon the right hand of him who sat upon the throne a book written inside and on the back, having been sealed with seven seals.'],
